The Dark Haired Girl is a collection of essays , poems and letters by Philip K. Dick .
Kingsblood Royal , a novel by American writer Sinclair Lewis , was published in 1947 .
The Golden Dog ( Le Chien d'Or ) was a novel by William Kirby ( 1817 - 1906 ) that was written between April 1869 and 1872 , with further revisions being up through 1876 .
A Song for Summer is a romance novel by British author Eva Ibbotson , first published in 1997 .
Sharp Edges is a contemporary romance written by Jayne Ann Krentz .
De zaak Natalee Holloway : mijn eigen verhaal over haar verdwijning op Aruba ( English : The Case of Natalee Holloway : My own story about her disappearance in Aruba ) is an autobiographical non - fiction book written by Joran van der Sloot with Zvezdana Vukojevic .
The Stories of English is a 2004 book by British linguist David Crystal ; it traces the history of the English language from the invasion of Great Britain by the Angles and Saxons in the 5th Century to the modern splintering of the language into its modern British , American , Indian , Australian , and other dialects .
The Cripple of Inishmaan is a dark comedy by Martin McDonagh who links the story to the real life filming of the documentary Man of Aran .
Reading Capital ( French : Lire le Capital ) is a 1965 work of Marxist philosophy by Louis Althusser , Étienne Balibar , Roger Establet , Jacques Rancière , and Pierre Macherey .
United States of Banana is a 2011 postcolonial dramatic fiction book by the Puerto Rican poet Giannina Braschi .
Hunter in the Dark is a young adult novel by Monica Hughes , first published in 1982 and has been the subject of school study .
A Thing of State is a 1995 political novel by Allen Drury which follows the U.S. State Department 's response to a crisis in the Middle East .
Zulu Heart is a 2003 alternate history novel by Steven Barnes , a sequel to the 2002 book , Lion 's Blood .
Lessons for Children is a series of four age - adapted reading primers written by the prominent 18th - century British poet and essayist Anna Laetitia Barbauld .
Elementos de derecho público provincial Argentino ( Spanish : Elements of Argentine provincial civic law ) is an 1852 Argentine book by Juan Bautista Alberdi .
Il Corbaccio , or `` The Crow '' , is an Italian literary work by Giovanni Boccaccio , traditionally dated c. 1355 .
The Right to Arm Bears is a collection of Gordon R. Dickson 's three science fiction novellas that occur on the planet Dilbia , where humans and an alien race known as Hemnoids are trying to win the support of the native bear - like population .
Dungeons & Dragons ( abbreviated as D&D or DnD ) is a fantasy tabletop role - playing game ( RPG ) originally designed by Gary Gygax and Dave Arneson , and first published in 1974 by Tactical Studies Rules , Inc. ( TSR ) .
Verbum Domini ( English : The Word of the Lord ) is a post - synodal apostolic exhortation issued by Pope Benedict XVI which deals with how the Catholic church should approach the Bible .
Recollections of a Tour Made in Scotland , A. D. 1803 ( 1874 ) is a travel memoir by Dorothy Wordsworth about a six - week , 663-mile journey through the Scottish Highlands from August--
Visions of Order ( 1964 ) is a posthumously - published work by conservative scholar Richard M. Weaver which argues that Western culture is in decline because many of its intellectuals refuse to believe in an underlying order of things -- in the way things are , irrespective of beliefs about them .
Madame de Mauves is a novella by Henry James , originally published in The Galaxy magazine in 1874 .
Broken Lives was written by Estelle Blackburn between 1992 and 1998 .
The Halloween Tree is a 1972 fantasy novel by American author Ray Bradbury which traces the history of Samhain and Halloween .
The Zenith Angle is a science fiction novel by Bruce Sterling , first published in 2004 , about a pioneering expert in computer and network security with a traditional hacker personality named Derek Vandeveer .
Život a dílo skladatele Foltýna ( Life and Work of the Composer Foltýn ) is an unfinished Czech novel , written by Karel Čapek .
The Fire People is a historical novel by Alexander Cordell , first published in 1972 .
The Nikopol Trilogy is a series of three science fiction graphic novels written in French by Yugoslavian born Enki Bilal between 1980 and 1992 .
Desert God is a novel by author Wilbur Smith first published in 2014 .
The Trial of Steven Truscott is a book written by Isabel LeBourdais , published in 1966 , on the trial and conviction of Steven Truscott for the murder of Lynne Harper in 1959 .
`` The Tyranny of Structurelessness '' is an influential essay by American feminist Jo Freeman inspired by her experiences in a 1960s women 's liberation group that concerns power relations within radical feminist collectives .
The Winds of Change and Other Stories is a collection of short stories by American writer Isaac Asimov , published in 1983 by Doubleday .
The Lady from the Sea ( Norwegian : Fruen fra havet ) is a play written in 1888 by Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen inspired by the ballad Agnete og Havmanden .
`` An Unfinished Race '' is a short story by American journalist and author Ambrose Bierce .
The Improvisatore ( Danish : Improvisatoren ) is an autobiographical novel by Hans Christian Andersen ( 1805 - -1875 ) .
Come in at the Door is the first book in Alabama author William March 's `` Pearl County '' collection of novels and short fiction .
From the Corner of His Eye is a novel by the best - selling author Dean Koontz , released in 2000 .
The Naïve and Sentimental Lover is John le Carré 's sixth novel and his only non - genre novel .
The Wurms of Blearmouth is the fifth novella written by Canadian author Steven Erikson , set in the world of the Malazan Book of the Fallen .
Darkness and the Light ( 1942 ) is a science fiction novel by Olaf Stapledon .
Midnight Nation is a religious - themed twelve - issue American comic book limited series , created by J. Michael Straczynski and published from 2000 to 2002 by Top Cow Productions under their Joe 's Comics imprint .
Of Grammatology ( French : De la grammatologie ) is a 1967 book by French philosopher Jacques Derrida that has been called a foundational text for deconstructive criticism .
`` Harvey 's Dream '' is a short story written by Stephen King , originally published in The New Yorker in June 2003 and later included in King 's short story collection Just After Sunset in 2008 .
`` The Shepherdess and the Chimney Sweep '' ( Danish : Hyrdinden og Skorstensfejeren ) is a literary fairy tale by Danish poet and author Hans Christian Andersen ( 1805 - -1875 ) .
Earth and High Heaven was a 1944 novel by Gwethalyn Graham .
Sefer Hamitzvot ( `` Book of Commandments '' ) is a work by the 12th century rabbi , philosopher and physician Maimonides .
Count Robert of Paris ( 1832 ) was the second - last novel by Walter Scott .
Tros of Samothrace is an historical novel with fantasy elements by author Talbot Mundy .
Nightmares & Dreamscapes is a short story collection by Stephen King published in 1993 .
Medicine Walk is a 2014 novel by Canadian First - Nations author Richard Wagamese .
Polish Logic is an anthology of papers by several authors , including Kazimierz Ajdukiewicz , published in 1967 and covering the period 1920 - -1939 .
The Club of Queer Trades is a collection of stories by G. K. Chesterton first published in 1905 .
`` The Scarlet Citadel '' is one of the original short stories starring the fictional sword and sorcery hero Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard and first published in the January , 1933 issue of Weird Tales magazine .
Alton Locke is an 1850 novel , by Charles Kingsley , written in sympathy with the Chartist movement , in which Carlyle is introduced as one of the personages .
The Nanny Diaries is a 2002 novel by Emma McLaughlin and Nicola Kraus , both of whom are former nannies .
After the Banquet ( 宴のあと , Utage no Ato ) is a novel by Yukio Mishima .
Armageddon 2419 A.D. is Philip Francis Nowlan 's novella which first appeared in the August 1928 issue of the pulp magazine Amazing Stories .
Vurt is a 1993 science fiction novel written by British author Jeff Noon .
`` Ode to a Nightingale '' is a poem by John Keats written in either the garden of the Spaniards Inn , Hampstead , London , or , according to Keats ' friend Charles Armitage Brown , under a plum tree in the garden of Keats House , also in Hampstead .
Las Dos Almas del Ser is a Spanish novel by Sigfrido Cuen published in 2011 .
Sonnet 128 is one of William Shakespeare 's Sonnets .
The Second Jungle Book is a sequel to The Jungle Book by Rudyard Kipling .
The Changing Light at Sandover is a 560-page epic poem by James Merrill ( 1926 - -1995 ) .
Gun Machine is a hardboiled detective thriller by English author Warren Ellis .
The Magic Strings of Frankie Presto is a novel by American author and journalist Mitch Albom .

My Darling , My Hamburger is a young adult novel written by Paul Zindel , first published in 1969 .
The Eye of the Sheep is a 2014 novel by Australian novelist Sofie Laguna which won the 2015 Miles Franklin Award .
Kapalkundala ( Bengali : কপালকুণ্ডলা ) , also known as Mrinmoyee , is a Bengali romance novel by Indian writer Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay .

A Romance of the Halifax Disaster ( 1918 ) is today a relatively rare novella by Lieutenant - Colonel Frank McKelvey Bell based on the Halifax Explosion of 1917 .
The Kraken Wakes is an apocalyptic science fiction novel by John Wyndham , originally published by Michael Joseph in the United Kingdom in 1953 , and first published in the United States in the same year by Ballantine Books under the title Out of the Deeps as a mass market paperback .
Majya Jalmachi Chittarkatha is an autobiography of Shantabai Kamble published in 1983 .
A Man Asleep ( French : Un homme qui dort ) is a 1967 novel by the French writer Georges Perec .
Waiting for Anya is a children 's novel by Michael Morpurgo , first published in Great Britain in 1990 , by William Heinemann .
The Dragon Who Ate His Tail is a collection of short stories , screenplay fragments and manuscript facsimiles by Ray Bradbury .
`` The Second - Richest Duck '' is an Uncle Scrooge comic book story written and illustrated by Carl Barks in February 1956 .
Beds in the East is the third novel in Anthony Burgess 's Malayan Trilogy The Long Day Wanes .
Year 's Best SF 12 ( ISBN 0 - 06 - 125208 - 5 ) is a science fiction anthology edited by David G. Hartwell and Kathryn Cramer that was published in 2007 .
The Intelligent Woman 's Guide to Socialism and Capitalism is a non - fiction book written by Irish playwright George Bernard Shaw .
Les Racines du mal ( `` the roots of evil '' ) is a 1995 crime novel by the French writer Maurice G. Dantec .
The Extraordinary Education of Nicholas Benedict is a novel by American author Trenton Lee Stewart .
`` Chanson d'automne '' ( `` Autumn Song '' ) is a poem by Paul Verlaine , one of the best known in the French language .

Smiles to Go is a 2008 young adult novel by Jerry Spinelli .
And the Land Lay Still is the fourth novel by Scottish novelist and poet James Robertson .
Asterix and the Falling Sky is the thirty - third volume of the Asterix comic book series , by Albert Uderzo ( story and illustrations ) .
A Meditation Upon a Broomstick is a satire and parody written by Jonathan Swift in 1701 .
Household Words was an English weekly magazine edited by Charles Dickens in the 1850s .
A Place Called Here is Irish writer Cecelia Ahern 's fourth novel , published in 2006 .
Juliet Dove , Queen of Love is a Magic Shop book written by Bruce Coville .
`` The Third Ingredient '' is a short story by O. Henry , notable for its ironic take on the `` Stone Soup '' theme .
William Carries On is the twenty - fourth book in the Just William series by Richmal Crompton .
The Ornithological Dictionary ; or Alphabetical Synopsis of British Birds was written by the English naturalist and army officer George Montagu , and first published by J. White of Fleet Street , London in 1802 .
Annie Dunne is a novel written by author and playwright Sebastian Barry .
A History of the Arab Peoples is a book written by the British - born Lebanese historian Albert Hourani .
Lion 's Blood is a 2002 alternate history novel by Steven Barnes .
The Naked Communist is a 1958 book by an ex FBI agent , United States author and political theorist W. Cleon Skousen .
History of Woman Suffrage is a book that was produced by Elizabeth Cady Stanton , Susan B. Anthony , Matilda Joslyn Gage and Ida Husted Harper .
The Colossus and Other Poems is a poetry collection by American poet Sylvia Plath , first published by William Heinemann , in 1960 .
Next Sunday is a collection of weekly essays by R. K. Narayan published in 1960 .
Dying of the Light is American author George R. R. Martin 's first novel , published in 1977 .
The Black Cloud is a science fiction novel written by astrophysicist Sir Fred Hoyle .
On Jungle Trails is a book - length compilation of Frank Buck 's stories describing how he captures wild animals .
Baker 's Biographical Dictionary of Musicians is a major reference originally compiled in 1900 by Theodore Baker , PhD , and published by G. Schirmer Inc. The publication is now in its ninth edition .
Une double famille ( A Second Home ) is a lengthy short story by Honoré de Balzac , which first appeared in 1830 under the title La femme vertueuse ( The Virtuous Woman ) .
Rockbound is a novel published in 1928 by Canadian writer Frank Parker Day .

Dariel : a romance of Surrey is a novel by R. D. Blackmore published in 1897 .
Children of Paranoia is a speculative fiction thriller novel written by Trevor Shane and published in September 2011 .
The Pathfinder , or The Inland Sea is an historical novel by James Fenimore Cooper first published in 1840 .
The Deadly Streets is a collection of short stories published by author Harlan Ellison in 1958 .
Popular Music from Vittula ( Swedish : Populärmusik från Vittula ) is a novel by Mikael Niemi .

Who Made Stevie Crye ? , subtitled A Novel of the American South , is a horror novel by author Michael Bishop .
Walk Two Moons is a novel written by Sharon Creech , published by Scholastic in 1994 and winner of the 1995 Newbery Medal .

Fire from Heaven is a 1969 historical novel by Mary Renault about the childhood and youth of Alexander the Great .
Fields Virology is an English - language virology textbook , published in two volumes , originally edited by Bernard N. Fields .
The Burial Mound ( Kjæmpehøjen ) was Henrik Ibsen 's second play and his first play to be performed .
The House on Mango Street is a 1984 coming - of - age novel by Mexican - American writer Sandra Cisneros .

At GenCon 22 in 1989 , Erick Wujcik introduced James Wallis to Kevin Siembieda of Palladium ; the result was Wallis ' entry into the world of RPG supplement publication through Mutants in Avalon ( 1990 ) .
Ulverton is the first novel by British author Adam Thorpe .
The New Tenant ( French : Le Nouveau Locataire ) is a play written by Eugène Ionesco in 1955 .

Writer of the Purple Rage is a collection of short works by American author Joe R. Lansdale , published in 1994 .
Colonel Jack is a novel by Daniel Defoe , first published in 1722 .
Entertaining Mr Sloane is a play by the English playwright Joe Orton .
An Apology for the Life of Mrs. Shamela Andrews , or simply Shamela , as it is more commonly known , is a satirical burlesque , a novella written by Henry Fielding , first published in April 1741 under the name of Mr. Conny Keyber .
Blue Willow is a realistic children 's fiction book by Doris Gates , published in 1940 .
The Lady of the Shroud is a novella by Bram Stoker , written in 1909 .
Too Far to Go is a collection of short stories by the American author John Updike published in 1979 in conjunction with the showing of a two - hour television movie on the NBC network with Blythe Danner , Michael Moriarty , Kathryn Walker and Glenn Close .
`` A Song for Simeon '' is a 37-line poem written in 1928 by American - English poet T. S. Eliot ( 1888 - -1965 ) .
`` The Hang of It '' is a short story by J. D. Salinger , first published in the July 12 , 1941 issue of Collier 's Magazine .
Blood tables : it is a holy action to kill Rosas ( Spanish : Tablas de Sangre : es acción santa matar a Rosas ) is an 1843 Argentine libelle written by José Rivera Indarte against the governor of Buenos Aires , Juan Manuel de Rosas .
Le Parole Obscure du Paysage Interieur ( The Obscure Speech of the Interior Landscape ) is a collection of French poetry by Italian esoteric writer Julius Evola , published in 1920 .
The Meursault Investigation ( French : Meursault , contre - enquête ) is the first novel by Algerian writer and journalist Kamel Daoud .
Life and Death in Shanghai is an autobiography published in November 1987(Published 1986 - 07 - 24 , ISBN 0 - 246 - 12948 - 4,ISBN 978 - 0 - 246 - 12948 - 2 ) by Nien Cheng from exile in the United States which details Cheng 's six - year imprisonment during the Cultural Revolution .
Human Punk is a 2000 novel by John King that tells the story of a group of boys who leave school in 1977 and the effect the emerging punk movement has on their lives .
The Deed of Paksenarrion is an epic fantasy saga by the American author Elizabeth Moon .
Sarah , Plain and Tall is a children 's book written by Patricia MacLachlan , and the winner of the 1986 Newbery Medal , the 1986 Scott O'Dell Award for Historical Fiction and the 1986 Golden Kite Award .
The Crystal Frontier ( Spanish : La frontera de cristal ) is a 1995 novel written by Mexican writer Carlos Fuentes .

The novel The Bladerunner ( also published as The Blade Runner ) is a 1974 science fiction novel by Alan E. Nourse .

The Saga of Cuckoo is a series of science fiction novels by Frederik Pohl and Jack Williamson .
Five Patients is a non - fiction book by Michael Crichton that recounts his experiences of hospital practices during the late 1960s at Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston .
The Only Possible Argument in Support of a Demonstration of the Existence of God ( German : Der einzig mögliche Beweisgrund zu einer Demonstration des Daseins Gottes ) is a book by Immanuel Kant , published in 1763 .

Cutting Through Spiritual Materialism , by Chögyam Trungpa is a book addressing many common pitfalls of self - deception in seeking spirituality , which the author coins as Spiritual materialism .

The Last Day of Creation ( in original German : Der letzte Tag der Schöpfung ) is a science fiction novel by German writer Wolfgang Jeschke , first published in 1981 .
The Geographical Dictionary of the Kingdom of Poland and other Slavic Countries ( Polish : Słownik geograficzny Królestwa Polskiego i innych krajów słowiańskich ) is a monumental Polish gazetteer , published 1880 - -1902 in Warsaw by Filip Sulimierski , Bronisław Chlebowski , Władysław Walewski and others .
La Ronde et autres faits divers is the title of a set of short stories written in French by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio and translated into English as The Round & Other Cold Hard Facts .
M. Butterfly is a play by David Henry Hwang loosely based on the relationship between French diplomat Bernard Boursicot and Shi Pei Pu , a male Peking opera singer .
Vampire Academy is an American best - selling series of six young - adult paranormal romance novels by author Richelle Mead .
The Commonwealth Saga is a series of science fiction novels by British science fiction writer Peter F. Hamilton .
Tuli ja raud ( English : Fire and Iron ) is a novel by Estonian author Karl Ristikivi .

The Tivington Nott is a novel by the Australian author Alex Miller and is based on the lives of real people in Somerset on the borders of Exmoor .
Confessions of a Crap Artist is a 1975 novel by Philip K. Dick , originally written in 1959 .
The American Political Tradition is a 1948 book by Richard Hofstadter , an account on the ideology of previous U.S. presidents and other political figures .
The Cat Who Went to Paris is a short novel by Peter Gethers that documents his life with his cat Norton , a Scottish Fold ( published in the UK as A Cat Called Norton ) .
The Swisser is a Caroline era stage play , a tragicomedy written by Arthur Wilson .
Tartuffe , or The Impostor , or The Hypocrite ( /tɑrˈtʊf , -ˈtuːf/ ; French : Tartuffe , ou l'Imposteur , pronounced : ( taʁtyf u lɛ̃pɔstœʁ ) ) , first performed in 1664 , is one of the most famous theatrical comedies by Molière .

Saint Joan of the Stockyards ( German : Die Heilige Johanna der Schlachthöfe ) is a play written by the German modernist playwright Bertolt Brecht between 1929 and 1931 , after the success of his musical The Threepenny Opera and during the period of his radical experimental work with the Lehrstücke .
The 2012 State of the Union Address was a speech given by President Barack Obama , from 9 p.m. to 10:17 p.m. EST on Tuesday , January 24 , 2012 , in the chamber of the United States House of Representatives .
The Ginger Man is a novel , first published in Paris in 1955 , by J. P. Donleavy .

Dichterliebe , ' A Poet 's Love ' ( composed 1840 ) , is the best - known song cycle of Robert Schumann ( Op . 48 ) .

Jessica Blandy is an ongoing Belgian comic book series , started in 1987 by Belgian artists Renaud and Jean Dufaux .
Magna Britannia , being a concise topographical account of the several counties of Great Britain ( to give its full title ) was an ambitious topographical and historical survey published by the antiquarians Daniel Lysons and his brother Samuel Lysons in several volumes between 1806 and 1822 .

Human Universals is a book by Donald Brown , an American professor of anthropology ( emeritus ) who worked at the University of California , Santa Barbara .

Shadowmind is an original novel written by Christopher Bulis and based on the long - running British science fiction television series Doctor Who .
The Watchers Out of Time and Others is an omnibus collection of stories by August Derleth inspired in part by notes left by H. P. Lovecraft after his death and presented as a `` posthumous collaboration '' between the two writers .
What Pet Should I Get ? is a Dr. Seuss children 's book , posthumously published in 2015 .

Cavedweller is the second novel from critically acclaimed author Dorothy Allison .
The American Pageant , initially published by Thomas A. Bailey in 1956 , is an American high school history textbook often used for AP United States History , AICE American History as well as IB History of the Americas courses .
Wanted for Murder is the title of a collection of six mystery novellas by Leslie Charteris which was first published in the United States in August 1931 .
The Prince of Wales and Other Famous Americans is a 1925 book by Miguel Covarrubias , a Mexican cartoonist .
Deutsch - Mythologische Landschaftsbilder is a two - volume book by Guido von List published in 1891 .
When the Moon Forgot ( originally published in Chinese as 月亮忘记了 ( The Moon Forgets ) ) is a children 's book originally written in Chinese by Jimmy Liao in 1999 .
Broom & Groom , by co - authors Pavan Choudary and Kiran Bedi , is a 2010 book on hygiene and manners intended to awaken `` the right to civic sense '' among the people of India .

Night of the Hawk is a 1992 Technothriller written by Dale Brown .
By Bizarre Hands Rides Again is a collection of short stories and two novellas written by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
A Course of Modern Analysis ( colloquially known as Whittaker and Watson ) is a landmark textbook on mathematical analysis written by E. T. Whittaker and G. N. Watson , first published by Cambridge University Press in 1902 .
Homer 's Daughter is a 1955 novel by Robert Graves , famous for I , Claudius and The White Goddess .
The Diana Chronicles is a 2007 British biographical book by Tina Brown that chronicles the life and death of Diana , Princess of Wales .
Une rose au paradis is a science - fiction novel written by René Barjavel , and first published in 1981 .

Son of a Witch ( 2005 , ISBN 0 - 06 - 074722 - 6 ) is a fantasy novel written by Gregory Maguire .
The Janissary Tree is a historical mystery novel set in Constantinople in 1836 , written by Jason Goodwin .

The Autobiography of Alice B. Toklas is a 1933 book by Gertrude Stein , written in the guise of an autobiography authored by Alice B. Toklas , her life partner .
The Year of the Intern , the first novel by Robin Cook and very different from his thrillers , follows the journey of intern Dr. Peters through his year of placement .
Queen Ann in Oz is a 1993 children 's novel written by Karyl Carlson and Eric Gjovaag , and illustrated by William Campbell and Irwin Terry .
Gunner Cade is the second of two science fiction novels written by Cyril M. Kornbluth and Judith Merril ( under their Cyril Judd pseudonym ) , originally serialized in Astounding Science Fiction in 1952 .
A Question of Blood is a 2003 crime novel by Ian Rankin .
S.A.M. is a French 4-issue comics series created by Richard Marazano and Shang Xiao .
The Impressionist is Hari Kunzru 's debut novel , first published in 2002 .
The House of Fame ( Hous of Fame in the original spelling ) is a Middle English poem by Geoffrey Chaucer , probably written between 1379 and 1380 , making it one of his earlier works .
Blue Gold is the second book in the NUMA Files series of books co - written by author Clive Cussler and Paul Kemprecos , and was published in 2000 .
The Poor Man and the Lady was the first novel written by Thomas Hardy .
Cursor 's Fury is a 2006 high fantasy novel by Jim Butcher .
Planet of Light , written by Raymond F. Jones , is a science - fiction novel first published in 1953 by the John C. Winston Co. as part of its 35-book set of juvenile novels .
Merlin 's Wood ; or , The Vision of Magic is a short novel written by Robert Holdstock and was first published in the United Kingdom in 1994 .
Hubert 's Hair - Raising Adventure is the first picture book published by author Bill Peet .
The Google Story is a book by David Vise and Mark Malseed that takes an in - depth look who founded the company and why it is unique .
Little Grunt and the Big Egg ( A Prehistoric Fairy Tale ) is a 1990 picture book written and illustrated by Tomie dePaola .
Wickett 's Remedy is a 2005 historical novel by Myla Goldberg , about the 1918 influenza epidemic .
Operación Masacre ( `` Operation Massacre '' ) is a nonfiction novel of investigative journalism , written by noted Argentine journalist and author Rodolfo Walsh .
Elmina 's Kitchen , first performed in May 2003 , is the fifth play from the British actor , playwright and broadcaster , Kwame Kwei - Armah .
Abie 's Irish Rose is a popular comedy by Anne Nichols familiar from stage productions , films and radio programs .
Dawn of the Arcana is a shōjo manga by Rei Toma first serialized in Monthly Cheese ! and licensed by Viz Media .
The Lawgiver is a novel by Herman Wouk , which the author published in 2012 at the age of 97 .
The Indigo Necklace ( 1945 ) , also published as The Indigo Necklace Murders , is a mystery novel by Frances Crane .
The Snail and the Whale is a children 's book by former children 's laureate Julia Donaldson , illustrated by longtime collaborator Axel Scheffler .
`` The Other Gods '' is a short story written by American horror writer H. P. Lovecraft on August 14 , 1921 .
Captain Underpants is a children 's novel series by American author and illustrator Dav Pilkey .
The Wonderful O is the last of James Thurber 's five short - book fairy tales for children .
Death of a Gossip is a mystery novel by M. C. Beaton ( Marion Chesney ) , first published in 1985 .
Ballad of Dog 's Beach ( in original Portuguese Balada da Praia dos Cães ) is a fiction novel by the Portuguese author José Cardoso Pires , relating the investigation into the murder of a political dissident , taking place around 1961 .
Bright April is a 1946 children 's story book written and illustrated by Marguerite de Angeli , who later won the 1950 Newbery Medal for excellence in American children 's literature for The Door in the Wall .
Tom 's Midnight Garden is a low fantasy novel for children by Philippa Pearce , first published in 1958 by Oxford with illustrations by Susan Einzig .
Ex - Mutants was a comic book series created by writer David Lawrence and artist Ron Lim along with editor David Campiti in 1986 .
How Obelix Fell into the Magic Potion When he was a Little Boy is an Asterix story written by René Goscinny and originally published in the French magazine Pilote issue 291 ( 1965 ) , with only a few drawings .
Complete Champion was written by Ed Stark , Chris Thomasson , Rhiannon Louve , Ari Marmell , and Gary Astleford , and was published in May 2007 .
`` Second Variety '' is a short story by Philip K. Dick first published in Space Science Fiction magazine , in May 1953 .
A Dead Man in Deptford ( 1993 ) was written late in Anthony Burgess 's life , and is the last of his novels to be published during his lifetime .
The Tarnished Eye is a 2004 crime novel by Judith Guest , based on the Robison family murders that occurred in June 1968 in Good Hart , Michigan and the murders committed by John Norman Collins in the Ann Arbor and Ypsilanti areas of Michigan in the late 1960s .
Paint Your Dragon is a humorous novel by Tom Holt first published in the UK in 1996 by Orbit and in paper back a year later by St. Martin 's Press .
Me and Earl and the Dying Girl is a 2012 debut novel written by Jesse Andrews .
`` The Unparalleled Adventure of One Hans Pfaall '' ( 1835 ) is a short story by Edgar Allan Poe published in the June 1835 issue of the monthly magazine Southern Literary Messenger , and intended by Poe to be a hoax .
Daisy Fay and the Miracle Man is a 1981 novel by best - selling author Fannie Flagg .
Relación breve de la conquista de la Nueva España ( English : Short Account of the Conquest of New Spain ) is the account of friar Francisco de Aguilar , who in his youth took part in the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire as a conquistador under the command of Hernán Cortés .
The Open Audio License is a free music license , created in 2001 by the Electronic Frontier Foundation ( EFF ) .
That Old Cape Magic is Pulitzer Prize - winning American author Richard Russo 's seventh novel .
Senselessness is the English translation of the 2004 novel Insensatez , originally written in Spanish by Salvadoran writer Horacio Castellanos Moya .
The Faiths of the Founding Fathers is a book by historian of American religion David L. Holmes of the College of William & Mary .
Wadzeks Kampf mit der Dampfturbine ( Wadzek 's Struggle with the Steam Turbine ) is a 1918 comic novel by the German author Alfred Döblin .
The Lollipop Shoes is a 2007 novel by Joanne Harris -- a sequel to the best - selling Chocolat -- continuing the story of Vianne Rocher , the chocolate - making character and Anouk and Rosette , her two daughters .
Psychology from an Empirical Standpoint ( German : Psychologie vom empirischen Standpunkte ) is an 1874 book by the Austrian philosopher Franz Brentano .
Mekanix is a six issue comic book limited series published in 2002 - 2003 by Marvel Comics , written by Chris Claremont , pencilled by Juan Bobillo and inked by Marcelo Sosa .
An Appeal from the New to the Old Whigs is a book written by the Irish Whig MP and philosopher , Edmund Burke , published on 3 August 1791 .
North from Thursday is a 1960 novel from Australian author Jon Cleary .
The Kingdom Keepers is a series of children 's novels written by Ridley Pearson .
`` The Bucket Rider '' ( `` Der Kübelreiter '' ) is a short story by Franz Kafka , written in 1917 .
The Mark of the Lion series is authored by Francine Rivers and consists of three novels :
Dinosaur Encyclopedia is an encyclopedia that was edited by Jayne Parsons .
The Sabre Squadron is Volume III of the novel sequence Alms for Oblivion by Simon Raven , published in 1966 .
Princess Priscilla 's Fortnight is a 1905 comedy - drama novel by the British writer Elizabeth von Arnim , known at the time as Elizabeth Russell .
Poison Elves is a black - and - white comic book by the late artist / writer Drew Hayes , concerning the life and times of an elf named Lusiphur .
Epilogue For W. H. Auden is a 76-line poem by Louis MacNeice .
Eye for Eye ( 1987 ) is a science fiction novella by Orson Scott Card .
The Book of Sand ( original Spanish title : `` El libro de arena '' ) is a 1975 short story collection by Argentine writer Jorge Luis Borges ( 1899 - -1986 ) .
Zen and the Art of Consciousness ( 2011 ) , originally titled Ten Zen Questions ( 2009 ) , is a book by Susan Blackmore .
Garden Spells is a 2007 novel by Sarah Addison Allen .
Days of Despair by Rajiva Wijesinha is a darker sequel to the author 's political comedy Acts of Faith which came out in the early years of the racial and political strife in Sri Lanka .
Rommel Drives on Deep into Egypt is Richard Brautigan 's eighth poetry publication and includes 58 poems .
Against the Day is a 2006 historical novel by Thomas Pynchon .
Beyond Culture is a 1976 book by American anthropologist Edward T. Hall .
`` Stellar Ships '' or `` Star Ships '' ( Russian name `` Zvezdnye Korabli '' , Russian : Звёздные корабли ) is a short story by the Soviet writer and paleontologist Ivan Yefremov written in 1944 and first published in 1948 in the USSR .
Where the Stress Falls , published in 2001 , is the last collection of essays published by Susan Sontag before her death in 2004 .
Three Essays on the Theory of Sexuality ( German : Drei Abhandlungen zur Sexualtheorie ) , sometimes titled Three Contributions to the Theory of Sex , is a 1905 work by Sigmund Freud which advanced his theory of sexuality , in particular its relation to childhood .
Middle - Age Spread is a 1977 play written by New Zealand playwright Roger Hall that premiered at the Circa Theatre in Wellington , New Zealand .
History of the Loss of Vietnam ( Chinese : 越南亡國史 ; pinyin : Yuènán Wángguó Shǐ , Vietnamese : Việt Nam vong quốc sử ) was a Chinese - language book written by Phan Bội Châu , the leading Vietnamese anti - colonial revolutionary of the early 20th century , in 1905 while he was in Japan .
Alireza , ( Persian : علیرضا‎‎ ) , is a memoir written by Iranian American author Arion Golmakani , translated into Persian by Shadi Hamedi and published in January 2014 .
An Indecent Obsession is a 1981 novel by Australian author Colleen McCullough .
Aurora Leigh ( 1856 ) is an epic novel / poem by Elizabeth Barrett Browning .
A quien corresponda ( To Whom it may Concern ) is an Argentine novel by Martín Caparrós .
Papegøien ( English : The Parrot ) is a farce from 1835 , written by Norwegian writer Henrik Wergeland under the pseudonym `` Siful Sifadda '' .
The Gods Themselves is a 1972 science fiction novel written by Isaac Asimov .
Altered Carbon is a 2002 hardboiled cyberpunk science fiction novel by Richard K. Morgan .
Players at the Game of People is a science fiction novel by John Brunner .
From the Earth to the Moon ( French : De la terre à la lune ) is an 1865 novel by Jules Verne .
The Land of Decoration is the debut novel by British author Grace McCleen published in 2012 by Chatto & Windus .
Skipping Christmas is a comedy novel by John Grisham .
The Courts of Chaos is the fifth book in the Chronicles of Amber series by Roger Zelazny .
Ungifted is a 2012 children 's novel by Gordon Korman .
The Master of Go is a novel by the Japanese author Yasunari Kawabata , first published in serial form in 1951 .
The Restaurant at the End of the Universe ( 1980 , ISBN 0 - 345 - 39181 - 0 ) is the second book in the Hitchhiker 's Guide to the Galaxy comedy science fiction `` trilogy '' by Douglas Adams , and is a sequel .
A Heart So White by Javier Marías was first published in Spain in 1992 ( original title Corazón tan blanco . )
Marazan is the first published novel by the British author Nevil Shute .
English Bards and Scotch Reviewers is a satirical poem written by Lord Byron .
Doctor Syn on the High Seas is the second in the series of Doctor Syn novels by Russell Thorndike .
Barrel Fever and Other Stories is a 1994 collection of short stories and essays by David Sedaris .
Is that a Monster , Alfie Atkins ? ( Swedish : Alfons och odjuret ) is a 1978 children 's book by Gunilla Bergström .
The Galilee Hitch - Hiker is Richard Brautigan 's second poetry publication .
Star Guard is a science - fiction novel written by Andre Norton and published in 1955 by Harcourt , Brace & Company .
Rain Stones is a 1991 short story collection by acclaimed Australian author Jackie French .
The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World : from Marathon to Waterloo is a book written by Sir Edward Shepherd Creasy and published in 1851 .
Anastasia at This Address ( 1991 ) is a young - adult novel by Lois Lowry .
Moon Base One is a young adult science fiction novel , the fourth in Hugh Walters ' Chris Godfrey of U.N.E.X.A. series .
Becket or The Honour of God ( French : Becket ou l'honneur de Dieu ) is a play written in French by Jean Anouilh .
Two Trains Running is a play by American playwright August Wilson , the seventh in his ten - part series The Pittsburgh Cycle .
3000 Years of Fantasy and Science Fiction is an anthology of fantasy and science fiction short stories , edited by L. Sprague de Camp and Catherine Crook de Camp .
The Diamond Smugglers is a non - fiction work by Ian Fleming that was first published in 1957 in the United Kingdom and in 1958 in the United States .
The Milltillionaire , or Age of Bardization is a work of utopian fiction written by Albert Waldo Howard , and published under the pseudonym `` M. Auberré Hovorré . ''
Van Loon 's Lives is a book by the Dutch - American writer Hendrik Willem van Loon published in 1942 .
The Rainbow Cadenza is a science fiction novel by J. Neil Schulman which won the 1984 Prometheus Award for libertarian science fiction .
The Boozer Challenge is a fiction book by author Charles Gill , son of famed New Yorker writer Brendan Gill , and brother of Michael Gates Gill , who wrote How Starbucks Saved My Life .
A Short Life of Kierkegaard is a book by Walter Lowrie , the first edition was published in 1938 by Oxford University Press simply under the title Kierkegaard .
`` Exile of Atlantis '' is a short story by Robert E. Howard and is the first story written by Howard to feature his creation Kull , set in his fictional Thurian Age .
City of Silence is a three - issue comic book limited series written by Warren Ellis and drawn by Gary Erskine .
`` The Martian Child '' is a novelette by American writer David Gerrold .
Foggerty 's Fairy and Other Tales is an 1890 book by W. S. Gilbert , collecting several of the short stories and essays he wrote in his early career as a magazine writer ( before 1874 ) .
A History of the Crusades , is a history of the Crusades and is arguably the best known and most widely acclaimed work of historian Steven Runciman .
On the Way to the Wedding is a historical romance written by Julia Quinn and published in 2006 .
Currant Events is the twenty - eighth book of the Xanth series by Piers Anthony , and the first book in the second Xanth trilogy .
Poor Charlie 's Almanack is a collection of speeches and talks by Charlie Munger , compiled by Peter D. Kaufman .
Het spook en de schaduw ( `` The ghost and the shadow '' ) is a novel by Dutch author Simon Vestdijk .
Hacker Culture is a cultural criticism book written by Douglas Thomas that deals with hacker ethics and hackers .
Mendy and the Golem , originally written by Leibel Estrin and later by Matt Brandstein , is the name of two American comic book series featuring Jewish characters .
The Gods Return is the ninth and final book in the Lord of the Isles Saga by David Drake .
The Healer 's Keep is the second novel in the Seer and the Sword series , by Victoria Hanley .
On Beauty is a 2005 novel by British author Zadie Smith .
The White Boy Shuffle is the 1996 first novel of poet Paul Beatty .
Jackson 's Dilemma is a novel by Iris Murdoch , published in 1995 .
`` The Gift of Gab '' is an early science fiction short story by American author Jack Vance , first published in 1955 .
Designing Virtual Worlds is a book about the practice of virtual world development by Richard Bartle .
Religion and Dharma ( 1915 ) is a book written by Sister Nivedita .
Something Leather is a novel - in - stories by Alasdair Gray which was published in 1990 .
Nepenthes of Mount Kinabalu is a monograph by Shigeo Kurata on the tropical pitcher plants of Mount Kinabalu and the surrounding area of Kinabalu National Park in Sabah , Borneo .
Hollywood Arms is a play by Carrie Hamilton and Carol Burnett .
Troubling a Star ( ISBN 0 - 374 - 37783 - 9 ) is the last full - length novel in the Austin family series by Madeleine L'Engle .
Arsène Lupin vs. Herlock Sholmes is a collection of two adventures of Arsène Lupin , written by Maurice Leblanc .
The Bridge trilogy is a series of novels by William Gibson , his second after the successful Sprawl trilogy .
Another Time is a book of poems by W. H. Auden , published in 1940 .
Scars of the Soul Are Why Kids Wear Bandages When They Do n't Have Bruises is a 2004 collection of essays by Miles Marshall Lewis .
Beyond Singularity ( ISBN 978 - 0441013630 ) is a science fiction anthology edited by Jack Dann and Gardner Dozois .
Witches of East End is a 2011 novel by author Melissa de la Cruz and the first entry in her Beauchamp Family series .
The Ragwitch is a young adult horror / fantasy novel written by Garth Nix .
A Prison Diary is a series of three books of diaries written by Jeffrey Archer during his time in prisons following his convictions for perjury and perverting the course of justice .
The Absentee is a novel by Maria Edgeworth , published in 1812 in Tales of Fashionable Life , that expresses the systemic evils of the absentee landlord class of Anglo - Irish and the desperate condition of the Irish peasantry .
All God 's Children Need Traveling Shoes , published in 1986 , is the fifth book in African - American writer and poet Maya Angelou 's seven - volume autobiography series .
`` There Will Come Soft Rains '' is a short story by science fiction author Ray Bradbury which was first published in the May 6 , 1950 issue of Collier 's .
An Officer and a Spy is a 2013 historical fiction thriller by the English writer and journalist Robert Harris .
The Queen of the Caribbean is a 1901 adventure novel written by Italian novelist Emilio Salgari .
The Dwelling - Place of Light is a 1917 best - selling novel by American writer Winston Churchill , the last of his twenty year run of best - sellers .
Red Azalea is a memoir of Chinese American writer Anchee Min ( b. 1957 ) .
Pan Podstoli ( Lord Steward , or Royal Pantler ) is a novel by Polish author , Ignacy Krasicki , published in several parts ( 1778 , 1784 and 1803 ) .
Monsieur Eek is a short novel by respected playwright David Ives , intended for ages 9 - -12 .
All the Names ( Portuguese : Todos os nomes ) is a novel by Portuguese author José Saramago .
The Devil Rides Out is a 1934 novel by Dennis Wheatley telling a disturbing story of black magic and the occult .
The Accidental Sorcerer is the first book in the Rogue Agent series by Australian writer Karen Miller .
The Bondwoman 's Narrative is a best - selling novel by Hannah Crafts , a self - proclaimed slave escaped from North Carolina .
Representative Men is a collection of seven lectures by Ralph Waldo Emerson , published as a book of essays in 1850 .
On My Walk is a young children 's book ( recommended for ages 2 - -5 ) by Kari - Lynn Winters and Christina Leist .
Leave Myself Behind is the 2004 debut novel by American writer Bart Yates .
The Immortal Beloved ( German `` Unsterbliche Geliebte '' ) is the mysterious addressee of a love letter which composer Ludwig van Beethoven wrote on 6 - -7 July 1812 in Teplitz .
The Chinese Maze Murders is a gong'an historical mystery novel written by Robert van Gulik and set in Imperial China .
The Chanur novels is a series of five science fiction novels , forming three separate stories , written by science fiction and fantasy author C. J. Cherryh and published by DAW Books between 1981 and 1992 .
`` Signs and Symbols '' is a short story by Vladimir Nabokov , written in English and first published , May 15 , 1948 in The New Yorker and then in Nabokov 's Dozen ( 1958 : Doubleday & Company , Garden City , New York ) .
Man 's Fate ( French : La condition humaine , `` The Human Condition '' ) , is a 1933 novel written by André Malraux .
`` The Cares of a Family Man '' ( `` Die Sorge des Hausvaters '' ) is a short story by Franz Kafka about a creature called Odradek .
`` Queen of the Black Coast '' is one of the original short stories about Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard and first published in Weird Tales magazine c. May 1934 .
Raptor Red is a 1995 American novel by paleontologist Robert T. Bakker .
The Supper of the Lamb is a food book by Robert Farrar Capon .
Anastasia Again ! ( 1981 ) is a young - adult novel by Lois Lowry .
The Return of Depression Economics and the Crisis of 2008 is a non - fiction book by American economist and winner of the Nobel Prize in economics Paul Krugman .
The Last September is a novel by the Anglo - Irish writer Elizabeth Bowen published in 1929 , concerning life at the country mansion of Danielstown , Cork during the Irish War of Independence .
A Satyr Against Reason and Mankind is a satirical poem by the English Restoration poet John Wilmot , 2nd Earl of Rochester .
Salt - Water Poems and Ballads is a book of poetry on themes of seafaring and maritime history by John Masefield .
Flood of Fire ( 2015 ) is a novel by Indian novelist Amitav Ghosh .
Suttree is a semi - autobiographical novel by Cormac McCarthy , published in 1979 .
The Nicomachean Ethics ( /ˌnɪkoʊˈmækiən/ ) is the name normally given to Aristotle 's best - known work on ethics .
A Summer Place is a 1958 novel by Sloan Wilson , a follow - on to The Man in the Gray Flannel Suit .
The Concept of Law ( ISBN 0 - 19 - 876122 - 8 ) is the most famous work of the legal philosopher H. L. A. Hart .
Life on the Mississippi ( 1883 ) is a memoir by Mark Twain of his days as a steamboat pilot on the Mississippi River before the American Civil War , and also a travel book , recounting his trip along the Mississippi River from St. Louis to New Orleans many years after the War .
The White Hotel is a novel written by the English poet , translator and novelist D. M. Thomas .
12 Who Do n't Agree ( Russian : 12 несогласных ) is a 2009 non - fiction book by the Russian writer Valery Panyushkin .
Doctor Slaughter is a novel by Paul Theroux published in 1984 .
Children Playing Before a Statue of Hercules is a 2005 anthology of short stories edited by David Sedaris .
A Trip Through Death , Sex , Divorce , and Spiritual Celebrity in Search of the True Dharma ( often referred to simply as Zen Wrapped in Karma Dipped in Chocolate ) is a book written by Zen priest and punk rock bassist Brad Warner .
Dark Valley Destiny : the Life of Robert E. Howard is a biography of the writer Robert E. Howard by science - fiction writer L. Sprague de Camp in collaboration with Catherine Crook de Camp and Jane Whittington Griffin , first in hardcover published by Bluejay Books in 1983 .
Abeltje is a children 's novel by celebrated Dutch author Annie M. G. Schmidt , originally published in 1953 by De Arbeiderspers .
Return to Groosham Grange ( also known as The Unholy Grail ) is the second Groosham Grange novel written by Anthony Horowitz .
`` A Letter from the Clearys '' is a short story written by Connie Willis published in the short story collections Fire Watch ( 1984 ) and The Best of Connie Willis ( 2013 ) .
Saintspeak ( 1981 ) is a satirical look at The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints by LDS author Orson Scott Card .
The Pollen Room ( German : Das Blütenstaubzimmer ) is the debut novel by Swiss author Zoë Jenny .
New Writings in SF 21 is an anthology of science fiction short stories edited by John Carnell , the last volume he oversaw in the New Writings in SF prior to his decease ; later volumes in the series were issued under the editorship of Kenneth Bulmer .
`` Half a Man '' is a song written by country music singer Willie Nelson .
Hafnia Hodierna , Eller Udførlig Beskrivelse om den Kongelige Residentz- og Hoved - Stad Kiøbenhavn ( English : Hafnia Hodierna , Or Detailed Description of the Royal Residence and Capital City Copenhagen ) is an engraved architectural work on Copenhagen , published by the Danish architect Lauritz de Thurah in 1748 .
The Autobiography of an Ex - Colored Man ( 1912/1927 ) by James Weldon Johnson is the fictional account of a young biracial man , referred to only as the `` Ex - Colored Man '' , living in post - Reconstruction era America in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries .
The Baltic Origins of Homer 's Epic Tales is an essay written by Felice Vinci , a nuclear engineer and amateur historian , published for the first time in 1995 .
General Systemantics ( retitled to Systemantics in its second edition and The Systems Bible in its third ) is a systems engineering treatise by John Gall in which he offers practical principles of systems design based on experience and anecdotes .
Crook as Rookwood is a 2005 Ned Kelly Award winning novel by the Australian author Chris Nyst .
The Light of Other Days is a 2000 science fiction novel written by Stephen Baxter based on a synopsis by Arthur C. Clarke , which explores the development of wormhole technology to the point where information can be passed instantaneously between points in the space - time continuum .
The Nature of Space and Time is a book that documents a debate on physics and the philosophy of physics between the British theoretical physicists Roger Penrose and Stephen Hawking .
Die Geschichte der Abderiten ( English : The Story of the Abderites ) , subtitled Eine sehr wahrscheinliche Geschichte ( English : A very probable story ) , is a satirical novel by the German poet and writer Christoph Martin Wieland .
Love and Glory ( ISBN 0 - 385 - 29261 - 9 ) is a 1983 novel by Robert B. Parker .
The Cheerleader is a 1973 coming of age novel by Ruth Doan MacDougall .
Balyakalasakhi ( Malayalam : ബാല്യകാലസഖി , meaning childhood companion ) , is a Malayalam romantic tragedy novel written by Vaikom Muhammad Basheer .
Big Susan is a 1947 children 's fantasy story written and illustrated by Elizabeth Orton Jones .
The Tempest is a play by William Shakespeare , believed to have been written in 1610 - -11 , and thought by many critics to be the last play that Shakespeare wrote alone .
Journey in North America ( original Hungarian title : Utazás Észak - Amerikában ) is a book by Sándor Bölöni Farkas published in 1834 .
If I Ran the Zoo is a children 's book written by Dr. Seuss in 1950 .
Mechanica ( Latin : Mechanica sive motus scientia analytice exposita ; 1736 ) is a two - volume work published by mathematician Leonhard Euler , which describes analytically the mathematics governing movement .
`` Eight Cousins , or The Aunt - Hill '' was published in 1875 by American novelist Louisa May Alcott .
Lectures on History and General Policy ( 1788 ) is the published version of a set of lectures on history and government given by the 18th - century British polymath Joseph Priestley to the students of Warrington Academy .
A guerra dos mascates is a novel written by the Brazillan writer José de Alencar .
`` The Mother Hive '' is a short story or fable by Rudyard Kipling about the decline and destruction of a hive of bees .
The Adventures of Luther Arkwright was a limited series comic book written and drawn by Bryan Talbot .
Jacob 's Rescue is a 1994 children 's book by Malka Drucker and Michael Halperin based on a true story that takes place in Warsaw , Poland during the holocaust .
M*A*S*H Mania is a novel written by H. Richard Hornberger under the pseudonym Richard Hooker and originally published in 1977 .
Summer 's Lease is a novel , set predominantly in Italy , by Sir John Mortimer , author of the Rumpole novels .
The Wimsey Papers are a series of articles by Dorothy L. Sayers published between November 1939 and January 1940 in The Spectator .
Sebastian O is a comic book series written by Grant Morrison , drawn by Steve Yeowell and published by the Vertigo imprint of DC Comics in 1993 .
On Your Toes ( 1936 ) is a musical with a book by Richard Rodgers , George Abbott , and Lorenz Hart , music by Rodgers , and lyrics by Hart .
Seetee Ship is the second of two science fiction novels by Jack Williamson , writing under the pseudonym Will Stewart .
The Waltz Invention is a tragicomedy in three acts written by Vladimir Nabokov in Russian as Izobretenie Val'sa in 1938 .
The Cure for Death by Lightning is the debut novel from Canadian author Gail Anderson - Dargatz .
Laura Warholic ; or , The Sexual Intellectual is a 2007 novel by Alexander Theroux .
Dr. Bloodmoney , or How We Got Along After the Bomb is a 1965 science fiction novel by Philip K. Dick .
The Clouds ( Ancient Greek : Νεφέλαι Nephelai ) is a Greek comedy play written by the celebrated playwright Aristophanes .
Published in 1976 , The Story of the Weasel is author Carolyn Slaughter 's debut novel .
The National Football Lottery is a book written by Larry Merchant , who is a sportswriter .
Liv till varje pris ( lit . Life to Every Price ) is a 2014 novel by Swedish author Kristina Sandberg .
Ice Station is Australian thriller writer Matthew Reilly 's second novel , released in 1998 .
Our Kind of Traitor is a novel published in 2010 by the British novelist John le Carré about a Russian money launderer seeking to defect to the UK after a close friend of his had been killed by the new leadership of his own criminal brotherhood .
The War of Anti - Christ with the Church and Christian Civilization is a book written in 1885 by an Irishman , Msgr George F. Dillon , DD .
Being Dead is a novel by the English writer Jim Crace , published in 1999 .
Lolly Willowes ; or The Loving Huntsman is a novel by Sylvia Townsend Warner , her first , published in 1926 .
`` The Story of an Hour '' is a short story written by Kate Chopin on April 19 , 1894 , and originally published in Vogue on December 6 , 1894 as `` The Dream of an Hour '' .
The Polish Officer ( 1995 ) is a novel by Alan Furst .
`` Just Before the War with the Eskimos '' is a short story by J. D. Salinger , originally published in the June 5 , 1948 issue of The New Yorker .
The Witch - Cult in Western Europe is a 1921 anthropological book by Margaret Murray , published at the height of success of the The Golden Bough by anthropologist James George Frazer .
`` The Reploids '' is an uncollected short story by Stephen King .
Dynamical Theory of Crystal Lattices is a book in structure theory of crystal lattices , written collaboratively by Max Born and Kun Huang .
Give Me Back My Legions ! is a 2009 historical novel by Harry Turtledove .
Whizzard ! is a 2002 fantasy novel written by Steve Barlow and Steve Skidmore , ( known as The Two Steves ) as the second part of the Tales of the Dark Forest series .
`` Oh , How I Miss You Tonight '' is a popular song , published in 1925 , written by Benny Davis , Joe Burke , and Mark Fisher .
Sironia , Texas is a novel by American author Madison Cooper that describes life in the fictional town of Sironia , Texas , in the early 20th century .
The Last Burden is a novel by Upamanyu Chatterjee that portrays life in an Indian middle - class family .
Mitch Owens has received the Polar Medal for his service in the Northwest Passage and the Royal Canadian Mounted Police Long Service Medal for his 21 years service with the RCMP .
James Leroy Bondsteel ( July 18 , 1947 -- April 9 , 1987 ) was a United States Army soldier who served during the Vietnam War , where he earned the Medal of Honor .
Evil Town was the last film with the actor Dean Jagger .
Educating Niní ( Spanish : Hay que educar a Niní ) is a 1940 Argentine comedy film directed by Luis César Amadori and starring Niní Marshall , Francisco Álvarez and Pablo Palitos .
Bolo ( 1613 - 52 ) , Abatai 's third son .
Elena Frías de Chávez ( born 1935 ) is the mother of late Venezuelan president Hugo Chávez , Aníbal José Chávez Frías and Adán Chávez .
Master Sergeant Juan E. Negrón ( September 26 , 1929 -- March 29 , 1996 ) was a member of the United States Army who served in the 65th Infantry Regiment during the Korean War .
Horst Hofmann ( 18 January 1919 in Cranzahl , Erzgebirge -- 14 June 1978 in Lübeck ) was a watch officer and coxswain on a Kriegsmarine U - boat in World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Wennersgaard Point ( 63 ° 51′S 59 ° 54′W ) is a point forming both the east side of the entrance to Lanchester Bay and the southwest side of the entrance to Jordanoff Bay on Davis Coast , the west coast of Graham Land in Antarctica .
Marcoux Nunatak ( 69 ° 55′S 159 ° 4′E ) is a nunatak 1,530 metres ( 5,020 ft ) high , about midway between the Schmidt Nunataks and Poorman Peak in the Wilson Hills of Antarctica .

Kamelen Island is an island about 45 metres ( 150 ft ) high , lying 6 kilometres ( 3 nmi ) southwest of the Einstøding Islands in the northern part of the Stanton Group , Antarctica .
Cape Yevgenov ( 69 ° 0′S 156 ° 36′E ) is an ice - covered cape midway along the northeast side of Krylov Peninsula , forming the west entrance to Lauritzen Bay , Antarctica .

The Kappen Cliffs ( 76 ° 56′S 162 ° 22′E ) are steep rock cliffs that form the south edge of Kar Plateau on Scott Coast , Victoria Land , Antarctica .

The Second Spanish Republic ( Spanish : Segunda República Española ) was the republican regime that existed in Spain from 1931 to 1939 , preceded by the Restoration and followed by Francoist Spain after the Spanish Civil War .

Taiwan under Qing rule refers to the rule of the Qing dynasty over Taiwan from 1683 to 1895 .
Seljuq Armenia refers to the period of Medieval Armenia under the Seljuq Empire , which began after its brief conquest by the Byzantine Empire with the fall of Bagratid Armenia in 1045 until the beginning of the Armenian - Georgian union in 1201 out of the turmoil of the fall of the Seljuq Empire in the same year .
The Taifa of Tortosa was a medieval taifa kingdom which existed for two separate periods : from 1010 to 1060 and from 1081 to 1099 .
The De Sanzy was a French automobile manufactured only in 1924 .
The Province of Brandenburg ( German : Provinz Brandenburg ) was a province of the Kingdom of Prussia and the Free State of Prussia from 1815 to 1946 , from 1871 within the German Reich .

The Taifa of Jerez was a medieval taifa kingdom that existed in what is now southern Spain in 1145 , until it was conquered by the Almohads .

The Kingdom of Cayor ( 1549 - 1879 ) was the largest and most powerful kingdom that split off from the Empire of Jolof ( Diolof ) , in what is now Senegal .

After a period in bankruptcy administration , Lola Cars International ceased trading on 5 October 2012 .

The Principality of Calenberg was a dynastic division of the Welf duchy of Brunswick - Lüneburg in the Holy Roman Empire from 1494 until 1705 , when Elector George I Louis , Prince of Calenberg , inherited the Principality of Lüneburg to form the state of Hanover .

Railtrack was a group of companies that owned the track , signalling , tunnels , bridges , level crossings and all but a handful of the stations of the British railway system from 1994 until 2002 .

Félix Galipaux ( 12 December 1860 -- 7 December 1931 ) was a French actor , playwright , and humorist .
Claude Farrère , pseudonym of Frédéric - Charles Bargone ( 27 April 1876 , Lyon -- 21 June 1957 , Paris ) , was a French author of novels set in such exotic locations as Istanbul , Saigon , and Nagasaki .
Lou de Laâge ( born 27 April 1990 ) is a French television , film and stage actress .
Roger Vincent ( 1878 - -1959 ) was a French actor who acted in over 100 movies over five decades .
Katja Suding ; born 30 December 1975 in Vechta , is a German politician of the Free Democratic Party ( FDP ) .

Frédéric de Courcy , born Frédéric Charlot de Courcy ( 16 August 1796 , Paris -- 6 May 1862 , Paris ) was a French man of letters .
Gilles Savary ( born 6 December 1954 in Oradour - sur - Vayres , Haute - Vienne ) is a French politician and former Member of the European Parliament for the Île - de - France .

Alain Le Vern ( born 8 May 1948 ) is a French Socialist Senator and is president of the Haute - Normandie region .

Jean - Michel Dupuis ( born in 1955 ) is a French theatre , TV and film actor .
Thomas Rosenboom ( born 8 January 1956 in Doetinchem ) , is a Dutch author of novels and short stories .
Ahmed Ben Messali Hadj ( Arabic : مصالي الحاج‎ ) ( 1898 in Tlemcen , French Algeria - June 3 , 1974 in Paris , France ) was an Algerian nationalist politician dedicated to the independence of his homeland from France .

Marc - Édouard Nabe ( born 1958 ) , whose real name is Alain - Marc - Édouard Zannini , is a French writer .
Melchior d'Hondecoeter ( c. 1636 -- 3 April 1695 ) , Dutch animalier painter , was born in Utrecht and died in Amsterdam .

Michaël Zeeman ( 12 September 1958 , Marken - 27 July 2009 , Rotterdam ) was a prominent Dutch journalist , author , editor , columnist and literary critic .
Annie Ducaux ( 10 September 1908 -- 31 December 1996 ) was a French actress , who appeared in 40 film and television productions between 1932 and 1980 .

Axelle Lemaire ( born 18 October 1974 ) is a French Socialist politician who currently serves as a Secretary of State in the French Government .

Jalil Shahnaz ( Persian : جلیل شهناز ) was one of the greatest maestros of Persian classical music and a virtuoso of the tar .
