Orthrosanthus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae first described as a genus in 1827 .
The Sulawesi hornbill ( Penelopides exarhatus ) , also known as the Sulawesi tarictic hornbill , Temminck 's hornbill or Sulawesi dwarf hornbill , is a relatively small , approximately 45 cm ( 18 in ) long , black hornbill .
In taxonomy , the Cladophorales are an order of green algae , specifically the Ulvophyceae .
The Tai forest tree frog , Leptopelis occidentalis , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Ivory Coast , Ghana , Liberia , and possibly Nigeria .
Araripedactylus was a large genus of pterodactyloid pterosaur , known from a single wing bone found in the Early Cretaceous - age Santana Formation of Brazil .
Amuropaludina is a genus of freshwater snails which have a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Viviparidae .
The Javan kingfisher ( Halcyon cyanoventris ) is a species of bird in the family Halcyonidae .
Peter 's wrinkle - lipped bat ( Mormopterus jugularis ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae , the free - tailed bats .
The Finlayson 's cave bat ( Vespadelus finlaysoni ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Anthropornis is a genus of giant penguin that lived 37 - 45 million years ago , during the Late Eocene and the earliest part of the Oligocene .
Achyrocline is a genus of flowering plant in the Asteraceae described as a genus in 1838 .
The Tsing - ling pika ( Ochotona huangensis ) is a species of pika endemic to the mountains in Central China .
Favolus , or honeycomb fungus is a genus of fungi in the family Polyporaceae .
Bagoinae is a weevil subfamily in the family Curculionidae .
The American badger ( Taxidea taxus ) is a North American badger , somewhat similar in appearance to the European badger .
Adenoncos is a genus of the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , consisting of 20 species native to Thailand , Vietnam , Malaysia , Indonesia and New Guinea .
Theragra finnmarchica or Norway pollock is a rare fish of family Gadidae ( codfish ) only known from the Barents Sea .
The common shrew opossums ( genus Caenolestes ) , are members of the Caenolestidae family .
Cyanotis ( syn . Tonningia ) is a genus of mainly perennial plants in the family Commelinaceae , first described in 1825 .
Leptotragulus is a small extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Protoceratidae , endemic to North America from the Eocene epoch ( Uintan to Chadronian stage ) 40.2 - -33.9 Ma , existing for approximately 6.3 million years .
Doratogonus is a genus of millipedes in family Spirostreptidae .
Libocedrus is a genus of five species of coniferous trees in the cypress family Cupressaceae , native to New Zealand and New Caledonia .
The Senegal chameleon , Chamaeleo senegalensis , is a species of chameleon native to West Africa .
Sansibia is a genus of soft corals in the Xeniidae family .
The Melanesian whistler or Vanuatu whistler ( Pachycephala chlorura ) is a species of passerine bird in the whistler family Pachycephalidae .
Williamodendron is a genus of evergreen trees belonging to the Laurel family , Lauraceae , in South America .
The Guadalcanal monkey - faced bat ( Pteralopex atrata ) is a megabat endemic to Solomon Islands .
Culicoides is a genus of biting midges in the family Ceratopogonidae .
The Aden Gulf torpedo ( Torpedo adenensis ) is a poorly known species of electric ray in the family Torpedinidae , seemingly endemic to the eastern Gulf of Aden , near the coast of Yemen .
The Gulf flounder ( Paralichthys albiguttata ) is a species of saltwater flounder .
Desmoderus variabilis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Desmoderus .
The Amargosa springsnail ( Pyrgulopsis amargosae ) is a snail in the family Hydrobiidae .
Vietbocap is a genus of troglobiontic scorpions in the family Pseudochactidae native to South - East Asia .
Doğramaci 's vole ( Microtus dogramacii ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Afrosphinx is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing one species , Afrosphinx amabilis , which is known from Zambia and the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Pteroinae is a subfamily of marine fish of the family Scorpaenidae .
The Burchell 's redfin ( Pseudobarbus burchelli ) , also known as Tradouw redfin , Tradou redfin or the Breede redfin , is an African freshwater fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Asolene is a genus of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
Apaturina is a monotypic genus of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae .
The genus Chenopodiastrum was described in 2012 by Suzy Fuentes - Bazan , Pertti Uotila und Thomas Borsch ( in : A novel phylogeny - based generic classification for Chenopodium sensu lato , and a tribal rearrangement of Chenopodioideae ( Chenopodiaceae ) . in Willdenowia 42 , p. 14 ) .
The Manicoré warbling antbird ( Hypocnemis rondoni ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
In the past the Kaibab squirrel was given species status ( Sciurus kaibabensis ) but today is considered a subspecies of the Abert 's squirrel , ( Sciurus aberti ) .
The Daraina sportive lemur ( Lepilemur milanoii ) is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Blanford 's pipe snake , Cylindrophis lineatus , is a species of snake in the Cylindrophiidae family endemic to Indonesia .
Dormer 's bat or Dormer 's pipistrelle ( Scotozous dormeri ) is a species of vesper bat .
Anthodiscus is a genus of plant in family Caryocaraceae described as a genus in 1818 .
The Arctomiaceae are a family of lichenized fungi in the Ascomycota , class Lecanorales .
Lachnocaulon ( bogbutton ) is a genus of plants in the Eriocaulaceae .
Icaricia is an invalid genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae now considered mostly synonymous with the genus Plebejus .
Haemodorum is a genus of herbs in the family Haemodoraceae , first described as a genus in 1798 .
Anoplodera pubera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Anoplodera .
Ictidodon and many other scaloposaurids are now classified as basal members of the clade Baurioidea .
Dendrodoris is a genus of nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Dendrodorididae .
Siphocranion is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1929 .
Lysapsus is a genus of frogs in the Hylidae family found in South America east of the Andes .
Suberites is a genus of sea sponges in the family Suberitidae .
Limacinae are a taxonomic subfamily of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Limacidae .
The Andaman serpent eagle ( Spilornis elgini ) is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
Taurocimmerites dublanskii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Taurocimmerites .
The bee tribe Ctenoplectrini of the subfamily Apinae , with the two genera Ctenoplectra and Ctenoplectrina , comprises 9 species in tropical Africa , 10 in Asia , and 1 in Australia .
The Cuban solenodon or almiqui ( Solenodon cubanus ) , is a species of soricomorph endemic to Cuba .
Sulphur - rumped tanager , Heterospingus rubrifrons Scarlet - browed tanager , Heterospingus xanthopygius
Brickellia is among the more basal lineages of the Eupatorieae and should not be assigned to a subtribe pending further research .
Chrysophyllum is a group of trees in the Sapotaceae described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Tornatellinops is a genus of minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusk , or micromollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
Gunnison 's prairie dog ( Cynomys gunnisoni ) is one of five species of the prairie dog .
Maués marmoset ( Mico mauesi ) is a marmoset endemic to Brazil .
The Archaeognatha are an order of wingless insects , also known as jumping bristletails .
Clanidopsis is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species Clanidopsis exusta , which is found from northern Pakistan ( Margalla Hills ) and north - western India , eastward along the southern slopes of the Himalaya to central Nepal and neighbouring parts of Tibet and Hubei in China .
Alnus nepalensis is a large alder tree found in the subtropical highlands of the Himalayas .
The Heteroptera are a group of about 40,000 species of insects in the order Hemiptera .
Argentine conger ( Conger orbignianus ) is a conger of the family Congridae .
Mynes is a butterfly genus in the Nymphalidae family found in Australia and Indonesia .
Erpobdella is a genus of leeches in the family Erpobdellidae .
Scotophilus Bat coronavirus 512 is a novel enveloped , single - stranded positive - sense RNA virus species in the Alphacoronavirus , or Group 1 , genus with a corona - like morphology .
The Blackfin poacher ( Bathyagonus nigripinnis , also known as the Blackfin starsnout poacher in the United States ) is a fish in the family Agonidae ( poachers ) .
Paraphungia laosensis is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Paraphungia .
Himantura is a genus of stingray in the family Dasyatidae , commonly known as the whiprays .
Belding 's ground squirrel was first described by Clinton Hart Merriam in 1888 , as Spermophilus beldingi .
Burchell 's starling or Burchell 's glossy - starling ( Lamprotornis australis ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
The Rzehakinidae was included in the Lituolacea , ( Textulariina ) in the Treatise Part C , 1964 , and removed by Loeblich and Tappan , 1982 to its own superfamily , the Rzehakinacea .
Pandoridae is a taxonomic family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalves in the order Pholadomyoida .
Collard greens ( collards ) are various loose - leafed cultivars of Brassica oleracea , the species which also contains vegetables including cabbage ( Capitata Group ) and broccoli ( Botrytis Group ) .
The Kokoda mogurnda ( Mogurnda lineata ) is a species of sleeper goby in the Eleotridae endemic to Papua New Guinea , where it is an inhabitant of clear streams in the rainforest .
Imma is a large genus of moths in the obtectomeran `` micromoth '' family Immidae .
Przevalski 's nuthatch ( Sitta przewalskii ) , originally given the nomen nudum Sitta eckloni , is a bird species in the family Sittidae .
Japanese green woodpecker or Japanese woodpecker ( Picus awokera ) is a medium - sized woodpecker similar and closely related to the European green woodpecker , but endemic to Japan .
Anaspis is a large genus of beetles belonging to the family Scraptiidae .
Aulacomya is a genus of edible saltwater mussels , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Mytilidae , the true mussels .
Bryant 's woodrat ( Neotoma bryanti ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Bythaelurus alcockii also known as the Arabian catshark is a catshark of the family Scyliorhinidae .
Mees 's white - eye ( Lophozosterops javanicus ) , also known as the Javan grey - throated white - eye or grey - throated ibon , is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
The Chinese red - headed centipede , also known as the Chinese red head , ( Scolopendra subspinipes mutilans ) is a centipede from East Asia and Australasia .
The specific name is derived from Peirosaurus , the type genus of the Peirosauridae to which specimens of Gasparinisuchus were initially assigned , and from Greek oid meaning form .
Bryophryne was erected in 2008 to accommodate two species that were in Phrynopus at that time ; subfamily Holoadeninae was erected at the same time and placed in Strabomantidae .
The Usambara weaver ( Ploceus nicolli ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
The Inca jay ( Cyanocorax yncas yncas ) is a bird species of the New World jays , which is endemic to the Andes of South America .
Helcogramma hudsoni , known commonly as the Hudson 's triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Helcogramma .
The Philippine spine - tailed swift ( Mearnsia picina ) , also known as the Philippine needletail , is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Diangathia bovifrons is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Swinny 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus swinnyi ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
Hesperolinon is a genus in the family Linaceae , whose common genus names are dwarf - flax or western flax , in reference to their distribution along the west coast of North America .
Ornithodoros is a genus in the soft - bodied tick family , Argasidae .
Glossata ( Fabricius , 1775 ) is the suborder of the insect order Lepidoptera that includes all the superfamilies of moths and butterflies that have a coilable proboscis .
The Bedriaga 's rock lizard , Archaeolacerta bedriagae , is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
Microstigmus is widely considered to be the only true eusocial species within the Crabronidae family .
Sudan plated lizard ( Gerrhosaurus major ) , also known as the Western plated lizard , great plated lizard or rough - scaled plated Lizard is a lizard of the Gerrhosauridae family .
The Mascarene swiftlet ( Aerodramus francicus ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Dimorphoptychia is the type genus of the subfamily Dimorphoptychiinae , which is likewise fully extinct today .
The Columbellidae , the dove snails or dove shells , are a family of minute to small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neogastropoda .
Paraulopus is the only genus in the family Paraulopidae , a family of grinners in the order Aulopiformes .
Androlepis is a genus of epiphytes in the botanical family Bromeliaceae , subfamily Bromelioideae , native to Central America and southern Mexico .
The Iago sparrow ( Passer iagoensis ) , also known as the Cape Verde or rufous - backed sparrow , is a passerine bird of the sparrow family Passeridae .
Margaret 's dragonet ( Callionymus margaretae ) is a species of dragonet native to the western Indian Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 22 to 107 metres ( 72 to 351 ft ) on sandy or muddy substrates .
Holland 's sportive lemur ( Lepilemur hollandorum ) , or the Mananara - Nord sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur that is endemic to Madagascar .
The Ecuadorian trogon ( Trogon mesurus ) is a species of bird in the Trogonidae family .
Vindula , commonly called Cruisers , is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Heliconiinae in the family Nymphalidae found in southeast Asia and Australia .
Haustellum is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
The Chinese scrub vole , or Irene 's mountain vole , ( Neodon irene ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Pyrrhocoroidea is a superfamily of true bugs in the infraorder Pentatomomorpha .
The Cameroon soft - furred mouse or Cameroon praomys ( Praomys morio ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Saccharomycetaceae are a family of yeasts in the order Saccharomycetales that reproduce by budding .
The Large - toothed conger ( Bathyuroconger vicinus , also known as the Largetooth conger or simply the Eel ) is an eel in the family Congridae ( conger / garden eels ) .
Tambja is a genus of colorful sea slugs , dorid nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the family Polyceridae .
The Arabian wheatear ( Oenanthe lugentoides ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Hymenocardia is a genus of trees in the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1836 .
Stigmatopelia is a bird genus in the pigeon and dove family ( Columbidae ) .
Macroplea is a genus of beetle of the subfamily Donaciinae in the family of leaf beetles .
The Florida woods cockroach ( Eurycotis floridana ) , palmetto bug , is a large species of cockroach which typically grows to a length of 30 - -40 mm ( 1.2 - -1.6 in ) .
Falkenstein 's greenbul ( Chlorocichla falkensteini ) also known as yellow - necked greenbul is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
Cedecea is a genus of extremely rare bacteria of the family Enterobacteriaceae .
Xylocaryon is an extinct plant genus in the family Proteaceae .
The New Zealand grebe , New Zealand dabchick , or weweia ( Poliocephalus rufopectus ) is a member of the grebe family endemic to New Zealand .
The Japanese squirrel ( Sciurus lis ) is a tree squirrel in the genus Sciurus endemic to Japan .
Handley 's slender opossum ( Marmosops handleyi ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Henosferidae ( also spelled `` Henospheridae '' ) is an extinct family of Australosphenida .
The Italian pool frog ( Pelophylax bergeri ) is a species of frog in the family Ranidae .
Incoltorrida madagassica is a species of beetle in the family Torridincolidae , the only species in the genus Incoltorrida .
Hyalinobatrachinae is a subfamily of glass frogs ( family Centrolenidae ) that was established in 2009 .
The Seychelles bronze gecko ( Ailuronyx seychellensis ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family endemic to Seychelles .
Macrostelini is a tribe in the Deltocephalinae subfamily of leafhoppers .
Glyphodactyla femoralis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Glyphodactyla .
Hammatoceratidae is a family of middle Jurassic ammonites included in the superfamily Hammatoceratoidea .
Castela is a genus of thorny shrubs and small trees in the family Simaroubaceae .
Axelrod 's rainbowfish ( Chilatherina axelrodi ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
Dennstaedtiaceae is one of fifteen families in the order Polypodiales , the most derived families within monilophytes ( ferns ) .
Acorimus problematicus is a species of beetle in the family Silvanidae , the only species in the genus Acorimus .
Gervais 's fruit - eating bat ( Artibeus cinereus ) is a bat species from South and Central America .
The Guadalcanal thrush ( Zoothera turipavae ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Japanolaccophilus niponensis is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Japanolaccophilus .
Lialis is a genus of lizards in the family Pygopodidae , with two member species in this genus .
Xainzanoceras , defined by Chen , 1987 , is a nautiloid cephalopod from the Upper Ordovician of China , assigned to the tarphyceratid family Lituitidae .
Triuridopsis is a genus of parasitic flowering plants in the family Triuridaceae .
Hypomesus is a genus of smelts ( Osmeridae ) , consisting of five species found in the northern hemisphere .
Hepatella is a genus of crabs in the family Aethridae , containing the following species : † Hepatella amazonica Beurlen , 1958 ( Lower Miocene ) Hepatella amica Smith , 1869 Hepatella peruviana Rathbun , 1933
Sanford 's white - eye ( Woodfordia lacertosa ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Neoraja is a genus of fish in the Rajidae family found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Cyclanorbis is a genus of softshell turtle in the Trionychidae family .
Subsequently it was found ( Xie et al . , 2009 ) that Rehmannia and Triaenophora are jointly the sister group to Lindenbergia and the parasitic Orobanchaceae .
Platycerioideae is a subfamily of the Polypodiaceae family of ferns .
Planchonia is a genus of trees and shrubs in the family Lecythidaceae first described as a genus in 1851 .
Bathyphytophilus is a genus of very small , deep water sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Bathyphytophilidae , the false limpets .
Eotomarioidea is an extinct superfamily of small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda .
Newton 's parakeet or the Rodrigues parakeet ( Psittacula exsul ) is an extinct species of parrot that was endemic to the Mascarene island of Rodrigues in the western Indian Ocean .
The Mokanga forest tree frog , Leptopelis fiziensis , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Tanzania , and possibly Burundi .
Kellen 's dormouse ( Graphiurus kelleni ) is a species of rodent in the family Gliridae .
Philorene texturata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Tetrasiphon is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Celastraceae containing the single species Tetrasiphon jamaicensis .
The Cretzschmar 's bunting ( Emberiza caesia ) is a passerine bird in the bunting family Emberizidae , a group now separated by most modern authors from the finches , Fringillidae .
Chelmonops is a genus of tropical fish in the family Chaetodontidae .
Pycnoptychia is a genus of a land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Urocoptidae .
Berryteuthis is a genus of squid in the family Gonatidae , comprising two known species .
The La Hotte bush frog or Baker 's robber frog ( Eleutherodactylus bakeri ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Massif de la Hotte in southwestern Haiti .
Loxogrammoideae is a small subfamily of the Polypodiaceae family of ferns .
Biretia is an extinct genus of Old World monkey , belonging to the extinct family Parapithecidae .
Idrissia is a primitive genus of the order Stomiiformes , and is an extinct relative of marine hatchetfish and viperfish .
The Oita salamander ( Hynobius dunni ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family endemic to Japan .
The Cape caco or Cape dainty frog ( Cacosternum capense ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
King penguin , Aptenodytes patagonicus Emperor penguin , Aptenodytes forsteri Ridgen 's penguin ( Aptenodytes ridgeni ) is an extinct species known from fossil bones of Early or Late Pliocene age .
Pareiorhina forms a monophyletic subunit with Neoplecostomus within the paraphyletic subfamily Neoplecostominae .
Xylocopa dejeanii , or Xylocopa ( Zonohirsuta ) dejeanii , is a species of carpenter bee .
Iophanus is a monotypic butterfly genus in the family Lycaenidae .
Baeopogon is a genus of songbird in the bulbul family Pycnonotidae .
The Alabama moccasinshell ( Medionidus acutissimus ) is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Chudeau 's spiny mouse ( Acomys chudeaui ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Mauritania and Morocco .
Flacillula is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) with five described species that occur in the Southeast Asian region .
The Rodrigues starling ( Necropsar rodericanus ) is an extinct species of starling that was endemic to the Mascarene island of Rodrigues .
Dorstenieae is a tribe within the plant family Moraceae .
The European roller ( Coracias garrulus ) is the only member of the roller family of birds to breed in Europe .
Among the Opisthothelae , the fangs of the Mygalomorphae point straight down in front of the mouth aperture and only allow the spider to grasp its prey from above and below , whereas in the Araneomorphae they face one another like pincers , allowing a firmer grip .
Macellocerus is a genus of darkling beetles in the subfamily Tenebrioninae .
The Empress of Germany 's bird of paradise , Paradisaea raggiana augustavictoriae , is a large , up to 34 cm long , maroon brown bird in the family Paradisaeidae , one of three families of birds known as birds of paradise .
Dromornis are part of a family of giant birds called Dromornithidae that lived from 8 million years ago until less than 30,000 years ago .
The Grenada flycatcher ( Myiarchus nugator ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Cimrmanium angulinotum is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Cimrmanium .
The Redeye bass ( Micropterus coosae ) is a species of freshwater fish in the sunfish family ( Centrarchidae ) native to the Coosa River system of Georgia , Alabama .
Andersen 's naked - backed fruit bat or Andersen 's bare - backed fruit bat ( Dobsonia anderseni ) is a large cave - dwelling species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The Rachel 's malimbe ( Malimbus racheliae ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Acmispon rigidus ( formerly Lotus rigidus ) , shrubby deervetch or desert rock - pea , is a perennial flowering plant in pea family ( Fabaceae ) found in the Mojave Desert and Sonoran Desert .
Afrothorictus latus is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Afrothorictus .
The Turati 's boubou ( Laniarius turatii ) is a species of bird in the Malaconotidae family .
Metasphecia is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species , Metasphecia vuilleti , which is known from Senegal .
Aplocera is a genus of moth of the family Geometridae .
The African harrier - hawk , harrier hawk , or gymnogene ( Polyboroides typus ) is a bird of prey .
Bcep78likevirus is a genus of viruses in the family Myoviridae , not assigned to a subfamily .
The Chinanteca salamander ( Bolitoglossa chinanteca ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Episacus pilosicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Episacus .
Pareuthria is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Rhizoprionodon is a genus of requiem sharks , and part of the family Carcharhinidae , commonly known as sharpnose sharks because of their long , pointed snouts .
Perissostomus palpalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Perissostomus .
Drascalia praelonga is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Drascalia .
Cypraeoidea , the cowries and cowry allies , is a superfamily of sea snails , marine gastropods included in the clade Littorinimorpha .
The Eyres skink , Oligosoma repens , is a nationally vulnerable species of skink native to New Zealand .
Speke 's pectinator or Speke 's gundi ( Pectinator spekei ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenodactylidae .
The Cyprus dwarf hippopotamus or Cypriot pygmy hippopotamus ( Hippopotamus minor ) is an extinct species of hippopotamus that inhabited the island of Cyprus until the early Holocene .
The Elgon shrew ( Crocidura elgonius ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Blepharipodidae is a family of sand crabs ( Hippoidea ) , comprising the two genera Blepharipoda and Lophomastix .
The Albanian water frog ( Pelophylax shqipericus ) is a species of true frog ( family Ranidae ) and is native to Albania and Montenegro .
Sykes 's nightjar or the Sindh nightjar ( Caprimulgus mahrattensis ) is a nightjar species found in South Asia .
Dietes is a genus of rhizomatous plants of the family Iridaceae , first described as a genus in 1866 .
The Bonneville whitefish ( Prosopium spilonotus ) is a salmonid fish endemic to Bear Lake on the Utah - Idaho border .
Vasinae , common name the vase snails or vase shells , are a taxonomic subfamily of large predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks within the family Turbinellidae .
Balticeras is an involute , discoidal Upper Jurassic ( Oxfordian ) ammonite ( order Ammonitida ) found in England , Germany , and Switzerland , belonging to the Perisphinctidae .
The Bornean bulbul ( Pycnonotus montis ) is a member of the bulbul family of passerine birds .
The Philippine long - fingered bat ( Miniopterus paululus ) is a species of bat from the family Miniopteridae .
Velinda lirata is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Velinda .
Thysanozoon is a genus of polyclad flatworms belonging to the family Pseudocerotidae .
The Foettingeriidae are a family of apostome ciliates of the order Apostomatida .
The Bokhara horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus bocharicus ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
Rhabdotus reflexus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Rhabdotus .
Periplomatidae is a family of large marine bivalves of the Pholadomyoida order .
The American rubyspot ( Hetaerina americana ) is a damselfly of the family Calopterygidae .
Cymbocarpa is a genus of flowering plants in the Burmanniaceae , first described as a genus in 1840 .

The Bahia heart - tongued frog , Phyllodytes melanomystax , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Roig 's pericote or Roig 's chaco mouse ( Andalgalomys roigi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Taliabu masked owl ( Tyto nigrobrunnea ) , also known as the Taliabu owl , or the Sula Islands barn owl , is an owl in the barn owl family , Tytonidae .

Melanodrymiidae is a family of gastropods belonging to the superfamily Neomphaloidea This family has no subfamilies .
Callionymus muscatensis , the Muscat dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the southern portions of the Red sea and the Gulf of Oman .
Entalinidae is a family of tusk shells , marine scaphopod mollusks in the order Gadilida .
The Nightingale Island finch ( Nesospiza questi ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae ( formerly in Emberizidae ) .
The Lesser Cuban nesophontes ( Nesophontes submicrus ) is an extinct species of soricomorph of the genus Nesophontes .
Euopisthobranchia is a taxonomic clade of snails and slugs in the clade Heterobranchia within the clade Euthyneura .
The Argentine angelshark ( Squatina argentina ) is an angel shark of the family Squatinidae .
Dicrostonychini is a tribe of lemmings in the subfamily Arvicolinae .
Heaviside 's dolphin ( Cephalorhynchus heavisidii ) , sometimes called Haviside 's dolphin after its discoverer , is a small dolphin found off the coast of Namibia and the west coast of South Africa .
Calcaritermes is a genus of termites in the Kalotermitidae family .
Stypopodium is a genus of thalloid brown alga in the family Dictyotaceae .

Lithagonum annulicorne is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Lithagonum .

The Hole - in - the - head frog ( Huia cavitympanum ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .

Neozavrelia is a genus of non - biting midges in the subfamily Chironominae of the bloodworm family Chironomidae .
Hydrophis nigrocinctus is a species of marine venomous snakes Elapidae ( Hydrophiinae - sea snake ) and Disteira nigrocincta is its synonym .
Acrorumohra is a fern genus in family Dryopteridaceae .
Anostoma , common name the up - mouth snails , is a genus of tropical air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Odontostomidae .
Inyoites is an ammonoid genus from the Lower Triassic , included in the ceratitid family Inyoitidae .
Lipandra polysperma ( Syn . Chenopodium polyspermum ) , common name manyseed goosefoot , is the only species of the monotypic plant genus Lipandra from the subfamily Chenopodioideae in the Amaranthaceae family .

Burmese trout ( Raiamas guttatus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Raiamas .

The Jelski 's chat - tyrant ( Ochthoeca jelskii ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .

Callionymus mascarenus , the Mauritius dragonet , is a species of dragonet endemic to the Indian Ocean waters around Mauritius .
Apterocaulus heterogama is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Apterocaulus .

Blyth 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus lepidus ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
Alopochen is a genus of the bird family Anatidae , part of the subfamily Tadorninae along with the shelducks .
Chascanopsetta is a genus of flatfish in the family Bothidae ( lefteye flounders ) found in deeper parts of the Pacific and Indian Oceans with a single species , C. lugubris also occurring in the Atlantic Ocean .
Leurocycloceras was assigned to Orthocerida by Sepkoski ( 2002 ) .
Westonoceratidae are exogastric , mostly compressed , Discosorida of moderate size from the Middle Ordovician to the Lower Silurian .
Saint Vincent 's bush anole or the Trinidad anole ( Anolis trinitatis ) is a species of anole lizard found in the Caribbean .
Stesichora is a genus of moth of subfamily Microniinae of Family Uraniidae .
Oplopanax is a small genus of flowering plants in the family Araliaceae , consisting of three species of deciduous shrubs , native to western North America and northeastern Asia .
The Javan mastiff bat ( Otomops formosus ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae endemic to Indonesia .
Goniatitinae is one of six subfamilies into which the Goniatitidae is subdivided according to Miller , Furnish , and Schindewolf , 1957 .
Baurusuchinae is one of two subfamilies of Baurusuchidae , the other being Pissarrachampsinae .
The Viverrinae represent the largest subfamily within the Viverridae comprising five genera , which are subdivided into 22 species native to Africa and Southeast Asia .
The Palawan striped babbler ( Zosterornis hypogrammicus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
The Sri Lankan junglefowl ( Gallus lafayettii ) , also known as the Ceylon junglefowl , is a member of the Galliformes bird order which is endemic to Sri Lanka , where it is the national bird .
Forsterygion gymnotum , known commonly as the Tasmanian robust triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Forsterygion .
The Pixie Grape is a new type of Vitis vinifera cultivar .
The Mindanao horned frog or Southeast Asian horned toad ( Megophrys stejnegeri ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Pachylebia pallipes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pachylebia .
Gigantophis is classified as a member of the extinct family Madtsoiidae .
The Leopard tortoise ( Stigmochelys pardalis ) is a large and attractively marked tortoise found in the savannas of Eastern and Southern Africa , from Sudan to the southern Cape .
The Rio Grande monkeyface ( Quadrula couchiana ) is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Wollaston 's roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros wollastoni ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .

Schneider , 1801 ( Halfmoon triggerfish ) Sufflamen fraenatum Latreille , 1804 ( Masked triggerfish ) Sufflamen verres C. H. Gilbert & Starks , 1904 ( Orangeside triggerfish )
The Asteriidae are a diverse family of Asteroidea ( sea stars ) in the order Forcipulatida .
Blind cave loach ( Nemacheilus troglocataractus ) is a species of troglobitic stone loach endemic to Thailand .
Nalpaumia septemstriata is a species of beetle in the family Latridiidae , the only species in the genus Nalpaumia .
Floridobia is a genus of very small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .
The Spix 's spinetail ( Synallaxis spixi ) , also known as the Chicli spinetail , is a bird in the ovenbird family .
Anaudia is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species , Anaudia felderi , which is known from Botswana .
The Fraser fir , Abies fraseri , is a species of fir native to the Appalachian Mountains of the Southeastern United States .
The Yankari shrew ( Crocidura yankariensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Helcogramma decurrens , known commonly as the Black - throated triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Helcogramma .
Hill 's shrew ( Crocidura hilliana ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Guam flycatcher or Guam broadbill ( Myiagra freycineti ) was a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Reflectopallium is a genus of air - breathing land slugs , specifically leaf - veined slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Athoracophoridae .
The Equisetopsida were formerly regarded as a separate division of spore plants and also called Equisetophyta , Arthrophyta or Sphenophyta ; today they have been recognized as rather close relatives of the typical ferns ( Pteridopsida ) and form a specialized lineage of the Pteridophyta .
The Paraguayan fat - tailed mouse opossum ( Thylamys macrurus ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Trachelophorus is a genus of weevils in the leaf - rolling weevil family Attelabidae .
Callionymus reticulatus , the Reticulated dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean and the Mediterranean Sea where it is found at depths of from 0 to 110 metres ( 0 to 361 ft ) .
De Witte 's clawed frog , Xenopus wittei , is a species of frog in the Pipidae family found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Rwanda , Uganda , and possibly Burundi .
The Culicinae are the most extensive subfamily of mosquitoes ( Culicidae ) and have species in every continent except Antarctica , but are highly concentrated in tropical areas .
The Cameroon racer , Poecilopholis cameronensis , is a species of fangless venomous snake endemic to Africa .
The Ryukyu black - breasted leaf turtle or Ryukyu leaf turtle , Geoemyda japonica , is a species of turtles in the family Geoemydidae ( formerly Bataguridae ) endemic to the Ryukyu Islands in Japan .
Bismarck 's trumpet - eared bat ( Kerivoula myrella ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Chlorellales are an order of green algae in the class Trebouxiophyceae .
C2likevirus ( synonyms c2-like viruses , c2-like phages ) is a genus of viruses in the family Siphoviridae , unassigned to a sub - family .
Austroraphidia is an extinct genus of snakefly in the family of Baissopteridae .
The Siamese mud carp ( Henicorhynchus siamensis ) is a species of freshwater cyprinid fish , a variety of Asian carp native to the Mekong and Chao Phraya Rivers in Southeast Asia , especially in Cambodia , Laos and Thailand .
Streptoprocne is a genus of swifts in the Apodidae family .
Megacamelus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore in the family Camelidae , endemic to North America from the Miocene through Pliocene 10.3 - -4.9 mya , existing for approximately 5.4 million years .
The Andean negrito ( Lessonia oreas ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Peters ' platanna ( Xenopus petersii ) is a species of frog in the Pipidae family found in Angola , Botswana , the Republic of the Congo , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Gabon , Namibia , Zambia , Zimbabwe , and possibly Tanzania .
Mapinguari desvauxianus was long known by the name Maxillaria desvauxiana Rchb.f .
Sugarcane smut is a fungal disease of sugarcane caused by the fungus Sporisorium scitamineum .
Junaphaenops tumidipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Junaphaenops .
Tullberg 's woodpecker ( Campethera tullbergi ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
The Angolan slender mongoose ( Galerella flavescens ) is a mongoose that lives in southern Africa , specifically Angola and Namibia .
Tapirus kabomani ( also known as the little black tapir or kabomani tapir ) is one of five extant species of tapir , large browsing mammals similar in shape to a pig .
Arenivaga is a genus of sand cockroaches , of the subfamily Polyphaginae , in the family Polyphagidae .
The Texas alligator lizard ( Gerrhonotus infernalis ) is a species of lizard in the subfamily Gerrhonotinae found in the central region of the American state of Texas , and south into Mexico .
Trichosilia was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a subgenus of Feltia .
Moltoni 's warbler ( Sylvia subalpina ) is a small typical warbler which breeds in Italy , Sardinia , southern France , southern Spain , and the Balearic Islands .

The Brazilian yellow - toothed cavy , Galea flavidens , is a cavy species from South America .
Cercamoniinae is a subfamily within the extinct primate family Notharctidae primarily found in Europe , although a few genera have been found in North America and Africa .

Coniogramme is one of three genera in the Cryptogrammoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae family of ferns .
Robynsiophyton vanderystii is a species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Kharmerungulatum is an extinct genus of Condylarth from the Late Cretaceous ( Maastrichtian ) Intertrappean Beds of Andhra Pradesh , India .
Cephetola nigra , Bethune - Baker 's Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The South American pilchard ( Sardinops sagax ) is a sardine of the Family Clupeidae , the only member of the genus Sardinops .
Setaro 's dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion setaroi ) is a species of lizard in the Chamaeleonidae family .
The Amsterdam wigeon ( Anas marecula ) , also known as the Amsterdam Island duck or Amsterdam duck , was a species of anatid waterfowl , endemic to Île Amsterdam ( Amsterdam Island ) , French Southern Territories .
The Indian longtailed sand - eel ( Bascanichthys deraniyagalai ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .

Trithrinax is a genus of few flowering plants in the Arecaceae family , that belong to the Coryphoideae subfamily , a not very evolved lineage .
The Buka Island solomys ( Solomys spriggsarum ) , also known as the Buka naked - tailed rat or Buka Island naked - tailed rat , is an extinct species of rodent known only from subfossil remains .

Nystiellidae is a family of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks within the superfamily Epitonioidea which includes the wentletraps , the purple snails and their allies .
Nephthytis is a genus of eight species of flowering plants in the family Araceae , native to tropical western Africa , with one species in Borneo .

Giganteopalpus is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species Giganteopalpus mirabilis , which is known from Sundaland .
The Táchira emerald ( Amazilia distans ) is a hummingbird described in 1956 by Alexander Wetmore and William Phelps as a new species from a specimen from Venezuela .

Meller 's duck ( Anas melleri ) is a species of the dabbling duck genus Anas .
Bradyodonti is an order of cartilaginous fishes ( class Chondrichthyes ) that lived in the Paleozoic Era .
Acrosterigma is a genus of large saltwater clams or cockles , marine bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
The Obi mosaic - tailed rat ( Melomys obiensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Taiwanese brown - toothed shrew ( Episoriculus fumidus ) is a species of shrew in the Nectogalini tribe .
The Hoogerwerf 's pheasant ( Lophura hoogerwerfi ) also known as Aceh pheasant or Sumatran pheasant is a medium - sized , up to 55 centimetres ( 22 in ) long , bird of the Phasianidae family .
Sehirus is a genus of burrowing bugs or negro bugs belonging to the family Cydnidae , subfamily Sehirinae .
The Malabar grouper or greasy grouper , Epinephelus malabaricus , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Captain 's wood snake ( Xylophis captaini ) is a species of snake described in 2007 , which is endemic to India .
The Bombay night frog ( also Abdulali 's wrinkled frog , Abdulali 's night frog , Humayun 's wrinkled frog ; scientific name Nyctibatrachus humayuni ) is a species of frog in the family Nyctibatrachidae .
Zimmer 's woodcreeper ( Dendroplex kienerii ) is a species of bird in the woodcreeper subfamily ( Dendrocolaptinae ) .
The American white pelican ( Pelecanus erythrorhynchos ) is a large aquatic soaring bird from the order Pelecaniformes .
The Congo sunbird ( Cinnyris congensis ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Petter 's soft - furred mouse , or Petter 's praomys ( Praomys petteri ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Caribbean flagfin blenny ( Emblemariopsis carib ) is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from tropical reefs in Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands , in the Caribbean Sea .
Okamejei pita also known as the Pita skate is a medium - sized skate in the genus Okamejei .
The Chipola slabshell , scientific name Elliptio chipolaensis , is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Tapeinochilos is a group of plants in the Costaceae described as a genus in 1869 .
Psegmatopterus politissimus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Psegmatopterus .
Wimanius is a mixosaurid ichthyosaur , and the only genus in the family Wimaniidae .
The Palawan horned frog ( Megophrys ligayae ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Apoanagyrus is a parasitic wasp genus in the family Encyrtidae .
In plant systematics Epidendroideae is a subfamily of the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Turbinellidae are a family of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the order Neogastropoda .
The Oldfield white - bellied rat ( Niviventer culturatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Corydioidea is a superfamily of insects in the order Blattodea , the cockroaches and termites .
Tonicia is a genus of chitons in the family Chitonidae .
The Kapala stingaree ( Urolophus kapalensis ) is a species of stingray in the family Urolophidae , endemic to inshore waters off southeastern Queensland and New South Wales .
Pelycodus is placed within adapiforms because of its annular ectotympanic , small eyes , non - elongated tarsus and numerous premolar and molar crests and within Notharctinae because of its four premolars , unfused mandible , a hypocone derived from the postprotocingulum and a lacrimal bone within the orbit .
Actinoleuca is a genus of sea snails or true limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Lottiidae .
Lates stappersii , the Sleek lates , is a species of lates perch endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Campbell 's dwarf hamster ( Phodopus campbelli ) is a species of hamster in the genus Phodopus .
The Bedford - Russell 's tree - nymph or Sulawesi tree - nymph ( Idea tambusisiana ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Eodiscina are mostly considered the more primitive suborder of the Agnostida , and the Agnostina the more advanced .
The Rothschild 's zokor ( Eospalax rothschildi ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae .
Xylomelum is a genus of six species in the plant family Proteaceae .
Mahehia is a genus of woodlice in the family Porcellionidae , which is endemic to the Seychelles .
Pantala is a genus of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae commonly called the Rainpool Gliders .
Allen 's big - eared bat ( Idionycteris phyllotis ) is a species of vesper bat .
Based on the partial fossils , Tochisaurus is thought to have been a member of the Troodontidae .
Actinodaphne is an Asian genus of the family Lauraceae , bay laurel - related , that comprises a group of flowering plants within the order Laurales .
Afrocarpus is a genus of conifers belonging to the family Podocarpaceae .
The Brazilian squirrel ( or Guianan squirrel ) ( Sciurus aestuans ) is a tree squirrel in the genus Sciurus endemic to South America .
The Himalayan beautiful rosefinch ( Carpodacus pulcherrimus ) is a true finch species ( family Fringillidae ) .
Cornulariidae is a family of soft corals in the suborder Stolonifera .
Wahlberg 's eagle ( Hieraaetus wahlbergi , formerly Aquila wahlbergi ) is a bird of prey .
Cephalantheropsis is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) , comprising 4 accepted species distributed in China , Japan , the Eastern Himalayas and Southeast Asia .
Liardetia is a genus of land snails in the family Euconulidae , the hive snails .
Christian Mayerhöfer ( born 16 June 1971 in Mainz ) is a German former field hockey player who competed in the 1992 Summer Olympics , in the 1996 Summer Olympics , and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Valentine Bialas ( January 10 , 1903 -- March 9 , 1965 ) was an American speed skater who competed in the 1924 Winter Olympics , in the 1928 Winter Olympics and in the 1932 Winter Olympics .
Alfred Klingler ( born October 25 , 1912 , date of death unknown ) was a German field handball player who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Krista Schmidinger ( born 18 May 1970 in Pittsfield , Massachusetts ) is an American former alpine skier who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics and 1994 Winter Olympics .
Nikola Kuljača ( born August 16 , 1974 in Belgrade , Serbia , SFR Yugoslavia ) is a Serbian water polo goalkeeper who played for the team of Federal Republic of Yugoslavia / Serbia and Montenegro on the bronze medal squad at the 2000 Summer Olympics and the silver medal squad at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Kazimierz Szosland ( February 21 , 1891 in Grzymaczew near Kalisz -- April 20 , 1944 ) was a Polish horse rider , major of the Polish Army , who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics and in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Ramón Duvalón ( born August 31 , 1954 ) is a retired boxer from Cuba , who represented his native country at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Flor - de - Lis is a Portuguese folk music group which represented Portugal at the Eurovision Song Contest 2009 in Moscow , Russia , following their victory in the 45th edition of Festival da Canção , with the song `` Todas as ruas do amor '' ( English : All the streets of love ) .
Dragoslav Ražnatović ( born 19 April 1941 in Vranje ) is a Serbian former basketball player who competed for Yugoslavia in the 1964 Summer Olympics and in the 1968 Summer Olympics .

Anna Báró ( October 3 , 1920 in Bajmok -- October 23 , 1994 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian stage , film , television and voice actress .

Daniel Nettelbladt ( 14 January 1719 , Rostock -- 4 September 1791 , Halle ) was a German jurist and philosopher .

Georg Karl Wilhelm Adolf Ebert ( 1 June 1820 , in Kassel -- 1 July 1890 , in Leipzig ) was a Romance philologist and literary historian from Austria .

Lauri Rapala ( 1905 , Sysmä -- 1974 ) , Finland , was the founder of Rapala - Normark Group , the world 's largest fishing lure and tackle producer .
Johan Jacob Döbelius , ( 29 March 1674 , Rostock , Germany -- 14 January 1743 , Lund , Sweden ) , was a professor of medicine .
Rafaela Aparicio ( born Rafaela Díaz Valiente ; 9 April 1906 -- 9 June 1996 in Madrid ) was a famous Spanish film and theatre actress .
Adolf Ziegler ( 16 October 1892 in Bremen -- 18 September 1959 in Varnhalt , today Baden - Baden ) was a German painter and politician .
Isidro de Alaix Fábregas , Count of Vergara and Viscount of Villarrobledo , ( 1790 Ceuta -- October 15 , 1853 Madrid ) was a Spanish general of the First Carlist War , supporting the cause of the Liberals , who backed Isabella II of Spain and her regent mother Maria Christina .
Heinrich Harder ( 2 June 1858 -- 5 February 1935 ) was a German artist and an art professor at the Prussian Academy of Arts in Berlin .
Julio Bolbochán ( Buenos Aires , 20 March 1920 -- Caracas , 28 June 1996 ) was the Argentine chess champion in 1946 and 1948 .
Georg Köberle ( 21 March 1819 in Nonnenhorn , on Lake Constance -- 7 June 1898 in Dresden ) was a German author and dramatist .

Karl Schapper ( December 30 , 1812 in Weinbach -- April 28 , 1870 , London ) was a German socialist and labour leader .
James Lackington ( 31 August 1746 , in Wellington , Somerset -- 22 November 1815 , in Budleigh Salterton , Devon ) was a bookseller who is credited with revolutionizing the British book trade .

Carl Beines ( 15 December 1869 in Rheydt , a borough of Mönchengladbach-7 October 1950 in Bad Wörishofen ) was a German violinist , who for ten years led the Gürzenich Orchestra in Cologne , as well as a pianist , composer , choir director and singing teacher .
Laci Boldemann ( 24 April 1921 in Helsinki -- 18 August 1969 in Munich ) was a Swedish composer of German and Finnish descent .

Henry of Bar ( c. 1362 -- October 1397 Treviso , Italy ) was lord of Marle and the Marquis de Pont - à - Mousson .
Hendrik Gerritsz Pot ( c. 1580 -- 15 October 1657 ( buried ) ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter , who lived and painted in Haarlem , where he was an officer of the militia , or schutterij .
Edwin Müller , later Edwin Mueller , ( December 2 , 1898 in Vienna -- October 4 , 1962 in New York City ) was an Austrian philatelist .

Fathi Arafat ( January 11 , 1933 -- December 1 , 2004 ) , born in Cairo , was a Palestinian physician and a founder and long - term chairman of the Palestine Red Crescent Society .
Paul Zweifel ( June 30 , 1848 , Höngg , near Zürich , Switzerland -- August 13 , 1927 , Leipzig , Germany ) was a German gynecologist and physiologist .
Valentin Vaala ( born Valentin Ivanoff ) ( October 13 , 1909 in Helsinki -- November 21 , 1976 in Helsinki ) was a Russian - born Finnish film director , screenwriter and edited .
Wilhelm Hasemann ( 16 September 1850 , Mühlberg - 28 November 1913 , Gutach ) was a German genre painter and illustrator .
Zheng Shiqi ( 1873 , Dingyuan , Anhui , China - 1935 , Jinan , Shandong , China ) , was a Chinese General , military governor of Shandong ( 1923 - -25 ) and Anhui ( 1925 ) .
Erwin Anton Gutkind ( May 20 , 1886 , Berlin -- 7 August 1968 , Philadelphia ) , was a German - Jewish architect and city planner , who left Berlin in 1935 for Paris , London and then Philadelphia , where he became a member of the faculty of the University of Pennsylvania .
Thomas Humphrey Cushing ( November , 1755 -- October 19 , 1822 ) was an officer in the Continental Army , and later the United States Army , and finally became a collector of customs for the port of New London , Connecticut .
František R. Kraus ( October 14 , 1903 , Prague - May 19 , 1967 , Prague ) was a Czechoslovak Jewish anti - fascist writer , journalist and editor .

Margaret Hendrie ( née Griffith , born 1935 ) was a writer from the Oceanian nation of Nauru .

Gregor Baumgartner ( born July 13 , 1979 ) is an Austrian former professional ice hockey winger who played the last 9 seasons of his career for EHC Black Wings Linz in the Erste Bank Eishockey Liga .
Anthony Fainga'a ( born 2 February 1987 ) is an Australian professional rugby union footballer .
The Atlanta Renegades Rugby Football Club ( also known as The ' Gades ) , founded in 1971 , is a premier D1 men 's rugby union team based in Atlanta , Georgia , USA .
Nathalie Dielen ( born March 18 , 1966 , 163 cm / 5'4 `` , 73 kg / 161 lbs ) is an athlete from Switzerland who competes in archery .
Maxim Rodshtein ( Russian : Максим Эдуардович Родштейн , Maksim Eduardovich Rodshtein ; Hebrew : מקסים רודשטיין‎ ; born 19 January 1989 in Leningrad ) is an Israeli chess grandmaster ( since 2007 ) .
Zoltán Halmay , who was a double Olympic champion , was the most successful sportsman in freestyle swimming .
A.S.D. Fersina Perginese is an Italian association football , and the major football club in Pergine Valsugana , Trentino - Alto Adige / Südtirol .
Born in Kongsberg , Asbjørn Ruud , with his brothers Birger and Sigmund , dominated international ski jumping in the 1930s .
Brydan Klein ( born 31 December 1989 ) is an Australian - born British professional tennis player .
Jan Gunnarsson ( born 30 May 1962 ) is a former tennis player from Sweden , who won one singles in Vienna in 1985 ( beating Libor Pimek in the final ) and nine doubles titles on the world tour during his professional career .
Delano Thomas ( born January 26 , 1983 in Berkeley , California is an American indoor volleyball player , who played as a middle hitter for the U.S. National Team . He was named Best Server at the 2007 Pan American Games , where Team USA claimed the silver medal in the men 's team tournament .
Bronta Laron Profit ( born August 5 , 1977 ) is an American professional basketball coach and former player .
Stephen Drew Sutton ( born June 30 , 1983 ) is an American former professional baseball infielder and outfielder .
Will Taʻufoʻou ( pronounced tau - FOE - oh ; born June 19 , 1986 ) is an American football fullback who is currently a free agent .
The 2011 Open de Nice Côte d'Azur was a men 's tennis tournament play on outdoor clay courts .
VC CSKA Sofia , is a professional volleyball team based in Sofia , Bulgaria .
Ammar Al - Tamimi ( born September 12 , 1988 ) is a professional squash player who represents Kuwait .
Reinhold Soyka ( born 22 March 1952 ) is a retired West German middle distance runner who specialized in the 800 metres .
The 2012 Valencia Open 500 was a men 's tennis tournament played on indoor hard courts .
Roberto Andrew `` Rob '' Sidoli ( born 21 June 1979 ) , also known as Robert Sidoli , is a former Welsh international rugby union player .
Leon Boyd ( born August 30 , 1983 in Vancouver , British Columbia ) is a Canadian - born Dutch baseball player currently playing for Corendon Kinheim in the Honkbal Hoofdklasse .
Henry Osinde ( born 17 October 1978 ) is a Ugandan - born Canadian cricketer who plays ODI cricket as a right - arm medium - fast bowler .
The Milwaukee Falcons were a minor league professional ice hockey team , based in Milwaukee , Wisconsin , that played in the International Hockey League from 1959 to 1960 .
Ng Tat Wai ( born 5 September 1947 in Penang ) was one of the top badminton players during the 1970s .
Penda Sy ( born April 29 1984 in Loudeac , France ) is a French basketball player who played 6 times for the French women 's national basketball team in 2004 .
The 1992 Benson and Hedges Open was a men 's ATP men 's tennis tournament held in Auckland , New Zealand and played on outdoor hard courts .
Bruttia Crispina ( 164 -- 191 AD ) was Roman Empress from 178 to 191 as the consort of Roman Emperor Commodus .
Phil Silvers was married twice , to Evelyn Patrick and to Jo - Carroll Dennison .
Doreen Hume ( born July 14 , 1926 ) is a Canadian soprano soloist who performed in North America and Europe from the 1940s through to the 1970s .
Antonietta Fricci ( born Antonie Frietsche ) ( 8 January 1840 -- 7 September 1912 ) was an Austrian - born opera singer known for her performances in leading soprano and mezzo - soprano roles in the opera houses of Europe .
